text_retweet:
#strongisthenewpretty #strongsmartbold #repost @mericherryla with @get_repost
・・・
how do you raise strong girls?
.
as a mom of two girls ages 6 and 7, i think about this a lot. i want to raise strong, confident, independent girls who believe in their voice and follow their dreams.
.
it’s not always easy but i try to lead by example, love myself and say nice things about myself, expose them to all kinds of ways of doing things and love up on them and what makes them unique.
.
this book by @katetparker does all those things through her gorgeous photography and quotes. my girls love reading each quote and hearing the names of the girls and their ages.
.
i put it on our holiday fave list (link in my profile) i’d love to hear how you raise strong girls. it feels more important than ever, from #metoo to braving natural disasters #woolseyfire , we need strength.

this is why we speak up.

their stories. her stories. our stories.

text_retweet:
#repost  @belinda_vegan all use of animals for food, clothing, entertainment, pets or experimentation involves utilising animals against their will, and - in the vast majority of cases - involves their suffering and deaths. we are brought up to believe in our current society that we need to consume or make use of other animals but this is neither ethical nor necessary. instead, vegans choose to live a lifestyle that respects other animals as sentient individuals whose lives have meaning and do not consume, wear or use animal products or take part in activities which exploit animals. today, being vegan is easy, proven to be healthy and needn't cost more. 
_
being vegan is about living a lifestyle that does not cause suffering, harm or death to animals, and allowing animals to be free to choose the way they want to live. other animals are sentient beings like us, with their own needs, desires and interests. we now know that like us, they can experience a wide range of sensations and emotions such as happiness, pain, pleasure, fear, hunger, sadness, boredom, frustration or contentment. they are aware of the world and what happens to them matters to them. their lives have intrinsic value - they are not inferior beings nor just here as resources or tools for human use. discriminating against non-human animals or believing them to be inferior solely because they belong to a different species is known as speciesism and is as unscientific and unjust as racism or sexism. 
_
embrace veganism🌱
www.govegannow.com

text:
legendary comic book icon stan lee, who pioneered the universe of superheroes with marvel comics, died on monday. as we mourn the loss of a great artist, we shouldn't negate that stan lee was accused of sexual misconduct by several nurses and a massage therapist earlier this year. in the age of #metoo we shouldn't forget that people in positions of power have misused their authority and it's important to take an account of the problematic things they did even if they created our favourite characters. 
we are not passing a judgement on the authenticity of the allegations, but merely acknowledging the serious accusations made against him. regardless of the creativity that stan lee brought into this world, we must remember the possibility of him being a predator because to look away or pretend otherwise would be disingenuous.

text: i'm really lucky to have met the friends i do know in this giant world. this point in history is horrifying for many in this country, and i'm grateful for the friends i do have, because there is weird tentions and insanity constantly in interactions. when i see people treat people of other colors unjustly, it's usually called out. even more, it reminds me, if i wasn't so pale, just a tint darker, whether it be a warm tone or more olive, cause i'm just very pale olive, so lebanese and olivey. that's how you'd treat me. that's how you treat humans. same with female harassment and assault. it doesn't matter who's more beautiful in the eyes of the predator (note: that a beholder isn't of mistreatment; a predator isn't a beholder). you mistreat a female, that's who you are. there's no competition, between females from my perspective, cause a man that mistreats a woman or child, i can't see as any type of leader. not qualified to run a house i live in and invite the friends i love to. so the priveleged people who don't stand up an acknowledge the wrongs, for their own protection, fuck you. never having to worry about politics because those laws you dont get affected by, you dont witness our oppression, murders? know that if they ever could do away with us, and they can't. say they did though; you'd be their first sacrifice. #freepress #metoo #blacklivesmatter #waterprotectors #thinkingboutmybestfriends

text:
[公共議題討論] 
今日整理資料、撰寫此文，小編心中亦是戒慎恐懼。因為本文的內容著實是「雙面刃」，雖點出現有未成年子女親權訴訟延伸的光怪陸離現象，但文章內容也可能給未來潛在當事人提供了有形無形的不當示範。但考慮許久，還是決定將這些發生在社會中的真實故事呈現出來：若還是不將親權爭議核心、即「當事人『搶小孩』動機」給消除，同住方為了控制住孩子、不讓孩子與探視方接觸，未來可能還會有各匪夷所思的怪招產生。 
各位讀者、網友若長期追蹤「紅鶴老爸陣線」就可知道，目前利用「家暴通報」「聲請保護令」當作家事訴訟「前菜」的文化很炙盛、基本上已經是「標配」，但更恐怖與冷酷的手法這兩年也開始增加了，即是提告「性侵」（通常是媽媽告爸爸對女兒性侵）用來當作離婚、剩餘財產、親權酌定案件的「帶風向」或者「拖時間」工具。本團隊近期接觸了兩位個案，分別是t先生、w先生，碰面與電訪後，將訪談資料整理為此文。以下是關於t.w.的故事。

關於t.w.的故事請參照：https://goo.gl/5dcvkz 
小編並不是呼籲要提高這類案件的提告門檻，因為這個社會確實有兒少因為親密或同住家屬的性侵而受害，體制當然要積極、快速、嚴格得處遇，來拯救所有可能受害的兒少。但當有心人利用制度上原本救人的工具、拿來害人時……似乎真的無法阻擋。另外t.w.都表示在社工訪談時，遭遇到社工相當高度的質疑與誤解……但如上述，因為社會上真的太多這類真實案件，社工真的不得不小心、以致於先入為主、有罪推定的文化已經固著了、無法改了。結果，幕後疑似誣告的加害者，可能在家納涼、吹冷氣看電視，而這些被告要東奔西跑、還要遭遇各式冷言冷語。「me, too」風潮仍在，我們必須鼓勵性侵受害者站出來揭發加害者！但我們也同時相信，利用體制與刻板印象、構陷他人性侵的惡質文化，也需要被遏止與批判！ 
以社會現實面跟統計數據來看，在各式親子組合當中，「父女」組合是最容易產生性侵、猥褻案件。所以屆臨家事訴訟的爸爸們，到底未來該怎麼探視女兒比較安全？怎麼防範，才能降低被誣告性侵呢？就小編目前所能想到的：
1、平時會面或交付後，當然要長期存有與女兒相處良好的影像紀錄。未來以備不時之需。
2、若支援系統足夠的話，爸爸們不妨請自己母親（孩子的奶奶）協助陪睡或幫忙女兒洗澡。減少攻擊方的著力點。
3、有項感覺比較瞎或尷尬的建議（但確實有個案這樣做）：就是每次交付孩子的當下、找個適合的地點，雙方進行孩子身體狀況的確認。這點主要用在「對孩子家暴傷害」之各類誣告或爭議。 ……小編想不到其他的了…..各位想法呢？ 
補充資料：針對未成年子女的訊問與調查，真的具有相當難度。有心人力不論利用此模糊空間，真的進行了性侵、猥褻，或者進行了性侵、猥褻的誣告，都讓調查訪視單位相當頭痛。早期國內並未有完整或專業的訊問程序，但近期針對刑事案件已經陸續建立、而且也慢慢引進到家事程序了，希望長期可以降低類似的誣告狀況。但小編還是由衷相信，要回到根源、從家事案件當事人的行為動機去改（最重要的一點是，落實「友善父母原則」），否則各類怪招真的沒完沒了，阻止了探視方與孩子的正常相處、也浪費眾多社會資源。

以社會現實面跟統計數據來看，在各式親子組合當中，「父女」組合是最容易產生性侵、猥褻案件。所以屆臨家事訴訟的爸爸們，到底未來該怎麼探視女兒比較安全？怎麼防範，才能降低被誣告性侵呢？就小編目前所能想到的：
1、平時會面或交付後，當然要長期存有與女兒相處良好的影像紀錄。未來以備不時之需。
2、若支援系統足夠的話，爸爸們不妨請自己母親（孩子的奶奶）協助陪睡或幫忙女兒洗澡。減少攻擊方的著力點。
3、有項感覺比較瞎或尷尬的建議（但確實有個案這樣做）：就是每次交付孩子的當下、找個適合的地點，雙方進行孩子身體狀況的確認。這點主要用在「對孩子家暴傷害」之各類誣告或爭議。 ……小編想不到其他的了…..各位想法呢？ 
補充資料：針對未成年子女的訊問與調查，真的具有相當難度。有心人力不論利用此模糊空間，真的進行了性侵、猥褻，或者進行了性侵、猥褻的誣告，都讓調查訪視單位相當頭痛。早期國內並未有完整或專業的訊問程序，但近期針對刑事案件已經陸續建立、而且也慢慢引進到家事程序了，希望長期可以降低類似的誣告狀況。但小編還是由衷相信，要回到根源、從家事案件當事人的行為動機去改（最重要的一點是，落實「友善父母原則」），否則各類怪招真的沒完沒了，阻止了探視方與孩子的正常相處、也浪費眾多社會資源。

[公共議題討論] 
今日整理資料、撰寫此文，小編心中亦是戒慎恐懼。因為本文的內容著實是「雙面刃」，雖點出現有未成年子女親權訴訟延伸的光怪陸離現象，但文章內容也可能給未來潛在當事人提供了有形無形的不當示範。但考慮許久，還是決定將這些發生在社會中的真實故事呈現出來：若還是不將親權爭議核心、即「當事人『搶小孩』動機」給消除，同住方為了控制住孩子、不讓孩子與探視方接觸，未來可能還會有各匪夷所思的怪招產生。 
各位讀者、網友若長期追蹤「紅鶴老爸陣線」就可知道，目前利用「家暴通報」「聲請保護令」當作家事訴訟「前菜」的文化很炙盛、基本上已經是「標配」，但更恐怖與冷酷的手法這兩年也開始增加了，即是提告「性侵」（通常是媽媽告爸爸對女兒性侵）用來當作離婚、剩餘財產、親權酌定案件的「帶風向」或者「拖時間」工具。本團隊近期接觸了兩位個案，分別是t先生、w先生，碰面與電訪後，將訪談資料整理為此文。以下是關於t.w.的故事。

text:
#sacred games actor #kubrasait has spoken in defence of co-star #nawazuddinsiddiqui after former miss india #niharikasingh accused him of #sexualharassment.

niharika #alleged that the #manto star, who she dated in 2009, forced herself on her at her apartment one day. “one morning, when i was home and he had been shooting all night, nowaz sent me a text saying he was near my building. i invited him over and asked him to come and have breakfast with me. when i opened the door, he grabbed me. i tried to push him away but he wouldn’t let go. after a little coercion, i finally gave in. i wasn’t sure what to make of this relationship,” she wrote.

the former miss india #claimed she ended the #relationship after she found out that the actor would frequently #lie to her.

however, #sait took to #twitter over the #weekend to defend her co-star and said, "a relationship gone sour isn’t #metoo, someone needs to recognise the #toxic difference before we go picking sides. i stand by #nawazuddinsiddiqui or #nowaz as a man."
#news #dbtv #dbtvlive
name: DBTV Live

text:
when crisis strikes, it destructs low energy patterns in your system. when it is a horrendously traumatic crisis, good news! you bet there’s so much to alchemise from that. storms not only dislodge trash and spread it around.. but new seeds too. ✨🌪✨ (it is not easy without sane people around you who walked the path themselves.) if you don’t know how to do that effectively, you sink into hopelessness and the toxicity begins to reintegrate into your system causing you relive aspects of that trauma. those sleepless nights is your soul keeping you awake to deal with the poison coursing through your body. resistance results in making you easy to trigger and the patterns taking time to settle, then show up and then analyze and dismantle and heal from and blah blah blah. “it takes time” (erm.. not necessarily 😉). that’s what is going on energetically: you bond on the level of the wound/shadow. very familiar story in these chaotic times. ( #metoo anyone?) all it takes is the realization that you simply weren’t vigilant in crafting yourself and blasting the shit out of the story at the critical point when the wound was fresh because you were caught in a blame cycle; the illusion that there is such thing as a victim. 
on that note... happy crisis anniversary to me. 2 years in a row i was released from jail on november the 13th. today, i am destroying every remaining shred of victimization and burden in my being. i command my body and dna to do so and remain vigilant in taking responsibility for the condition of my reality. no longer available to bullshit. nothing and no one has power over me (or you). 🌼⚡️💩⚡️🌼 #energyalchemy #metoomovementofthedark #alchemy
name: Zoë 🐇🔥

text:
stop saying this nonsense. “rapists are not real men, they are animals” 
it is reductionist, patronizing, and insulting to survivors. the men who rape the  women who tell their stories on social media are human men. they are real, they aren’t ghosts, neither are they aliens. they don’t just drop from outer space, they grow up among us.
rapists don’t come from a vacuum. they are not animals in the forest, neither are they aliens. they are the men in our homes, schools, hospitals, churches, at the cornerstore, the drivers, domestic helps etc. they are men. they are human men socialized to think they can take from women, violate women, mistreat women, dehumanize women, and so they do. stop disassociating them from our species as if they are not a part of it. rapists are a patriarchal human creation. and anyone upholding the patriarchy is responsible. this is on all of you.

text:
in 2017, a major increase in men and women started to speak up regarding their previous harassment encounters. however, men were quickly shamed and look down on for speaking up. but, a few years ago men and women thought it was pointless to pursue justice against their sexual harassers. now that they speak up to make a better tomorrow they are shut down. in fact, a study in 2015 unveiled that one-third of women ages 18 to 34 had experienced sexual harassment at work. and 71 percent did not report it. the fear of reporting it and justifying what has happened to them overcomes their instincts. for example, a person could be publicly against sexual harassment, until they get harassed and they are silent. the guilt, the thought that it is their fault, and so much more takes over their mind. however, recently, social media has risen and begun to address these issues. men and women around the world began to share their stories with the #metoo movement that started in hollywood but spread internationally. spanish countries had the #yotambién, and france begun the #balancetonporc (call out your pig). the # of one brave woman led to millions around the world to speak up. constantly victims feel the need to stay silent and covered but that should not be the case. speak up for yourself, and if you can't, do not worry, the rest of us will.
#metoo #yotambién #balancetonporc

"he was emotionally and physically abusive. he would berate me or call other women on the phone to upset me. one day i confronted him while he was doing that and he yanked the phone from me and bit me. .
.
then one day, he decided to torture me. he tried to drown me by holding my head under cold water for various lengths of time.  he folded my arm so hard behind my back that i thought he would break it, and he  beat me with a belt. when he finally stopped i didn't say anything, i just left the house like i was going to the store. but instead i walked to the nearest police station so i could report him and ask the cops to go get him out of my house.
.
.
he came back later that night and banged on my front door for about an hour, but i never relented, and since that day i've never looked back." ... ©anonymous
.
.

text:
i haven’t posted in a long time... why? because i recently got married to the love of my life and i am over the moon. but that’s not all... why am i posting now? i feel that i have to share what has changed in my life.  first off, i married a unicorn, yes, i said it “unicorn”, or as i like to call him “my unicorn husband”. my husband is the most understanding, supportive, hard working, loving, caring man i have ever met in my life!  not one bit of him is selfish.  i wish he could be a bit selfish because he deserves to be. he makes me want to be a better person, a better wife, each and every day. 
i do have some bad days... days when i think about the past and beat myself up for not being good enough.  a short conversation can trigger past thoughts... i immediately shut down. 
those who are close to me know that hot yoga has changed my life.  i have tried many classes and i found that @lisapyoga is my favourite coach/trainer/guide/mentor and now a friend. 
i have never introduced myself to lisa.  i attend her classes every wednesday and saturday and i leave right away, tears rolling down my cheeks, soaked in sweat... complete zen... i knew after lisa’s first class that there was something connecting us... i couldn’t figure it out until i found lisa on instagram and then, her website.  i read lisa’s story and i immediately teared up. i cried sad tears and then, finally happy tears... this wednesday i will finally get the courage to introduce myself, rather than rushing out of class so that nobody sees the tears rolling down my cheeks, the sweat dripping down my body and the mascara running down my face. 
it’s amazing what just one person can do to make a difference in your life.  whether it be positive or negative. take some time to think about who is negative in your life... and rather, choose those who make you smile, laugh and feel loved ❤️
#metoo #sexualassault #survivor #photoshoot #espys #yoga #yogi #fitness

text: see what people are saying about candy apple butterscotch, #newauthor rebecca macceile’s debut publication. “this is an impactful read if you have ever experienced any sort of abuse. i appreciate the author’s candor and willingness to write with such openness. she takes responsibility for herself as much as she describes the lasting effects of trauma.” “it is worth the read. it’s about a woman empowered and, my god, that is a wonderful thing indeed.” “the author gets to the point while still painting a very clear and definite picture for the readers and i love that. the accounts of the trauma are laid out in such a way that you know what’s happening and are able to imagine it but you aren’t bombarded with intense graphic imagery, which i appreciate as a survivor myself. would definitely recommend!” “this amazingly written gem takes you inside the author’s world and keeps you there, making you feel like a discreet “bug on the wall.” i could not put it down.” “i wish everyone would write a memoir. it would be so much easier to understand people. i haven’t been through anything as violent or traumatic, but i think this story is relatable in a lot of ways. it just makes me see a lot of things differently in every day life. it’s a big eye opener.” #onsalenow at the #linkinbio. #kindle and #paperback versions available! also for members of #amazonprime, candy apple butterscotch is available in the #kindlelendinglibrary as well as through #kindleunlimitedbooks! that’s right you can read for #free. #nonfictionbooks #memoir #metoo #ptsdsurvivor #kindlestoryteller2018  #kindledirectpublishing #onsalenow #paperback #kindlelendinglibrary #bookrecommendations #indieauthor #authorsofinstagram #amazon #readforfreekll

text: my kids love @thebucketlistfamily so much that they routinely walk around our home with their backpacks on pretending to travel to different places. today they told me they were walking from nyc to bhutan. i reminded them of the ocean they would need to cross and told them to be sure to charter a boat. instead they decided to get their swimsuits on and swim to bhutan! then winston had his hair shaved like @manillagee and @garrettgee. and, chandler is calling herself @dorothygee now while she carries around her doll named @caligee. i guess that makes me @jessgee! they've found an airplane to fly them back to the us so they can go to disney.  #welovethebucketlistfamily #thebucketlistfamily #travelwithkids #mykidswanttoseetheworld #metoo #chandlergrace #winstonasante

text:
a little over nine years ago these ladies in the picture were lifeguards and also roomies in an apartment on turnabout lane. they would share their dreams and experiences, fight about dirty dishes, steal each other's food and tolerate each other's snoring (not mine - guess whose 😄), dole out dating advice and become die-hard fans of estelle's "american boy"... first real jobs, first responsibilities, first paychecks, first disillusionment over the english language they thought they'd known 😄
.
it's been a lifetime ever since, and honestly i didn't hope to get the three of us in the same picture again any time soon. but here we are! as young and beautiful and smart-ass as ever. okay, just smart 😁
.
and no matter how much time goes by, it's about the feeling. that feeling when you can pick it up exactly where you left it off. cheers to keeping in touch with old friends and to happy-go-lucky selfies in the coming years! ☺

text:
do you love yourself? i mean really? do you nurture this love? can you list reasons why you’re in love? can you go down to the comments and tell me a couple reasons right now? do it now, please, it could help someone else reading this... ♥️♥️ i love myself, no matter what. yesterday a family member called me angry and unfollowed me on facebook. but it’s ok, because i love my anger too. my anger is correct. society and the power structures of organized religion and heterosexual patriarchy did a lot of damage to me. but also, i suspect, to this family member. there is a difference between anger and hate, as i recently heard the brilliant @rachel.cargle say. and she really spoke right to my heart when she said: ‘i won’t stop fighting. i will move forward with a righteous anger and a fiery passion — always.’ ♥️ i love that my heart and mind are seeking to be kinder and gentler. i love that this seeking includes the need for justice. through justice recovery can begin and i love that i am healing and able to encourage healing in others. i love that i see a truth, which is that we heal all together or not at all. i love that i have found inspiration in a world that once seemed so bleak. i love that i am standing up to the powers that have always been and saying loudly and with that fiery passion: you will not always be. •
•
#blacklivesmatter #metoo #transisbeautiful #lgbtq #womensrightsarehumanrights #indiginouspride #slaythepatriarchy #itsallconnected

text:
sp whotehall os loke civil servants, that's government warning workers headquarters. 
hundreds of civil servants working in whitehall have made complaints about suffering sexual harassment or bullying at the hands of colleagues – but only a fraction of staff have faced disciplinary action.

a guardian investigation using freedom of information laws reveals that government departments and other publicly funded bodies have received at least 551 complaints from staff who say they have been victims of sexual harassment or bullying over the past three years. that figure includes 95 staff who have complained about being sexually harassed.

yet in scores of cases staff have apparently not faced disciplinary investigations as a result of the complaints, with dozens more of those accused of misconduct escaping any kind of punishment.

the true number of staff raising harassment and bullying grievances is likely to be even higher as only 21 government departments and taxpayer-funded bodies provided data, with many claiming they were unable to supply information.

for example, from 2016-18 at hmrc, when there were 294 bullying complaints, 10 or fewer men and 10 or fewer women were subjected to disciplinary investigations in any one year.

in 2016, when 13 male and less than 10 female cps staff made bullying complaints, not a single member of staff faced a disciplinary investigation.

there have been growing concerns over bullying and sexual harassment in the workplace since the #metoo campaign. a damning independent report by dame laura cox published last month laid bare a culture of bullying and harassment in the house of commons, concluding there was a tradition of “deference and silence” that “actively sought to cover up abusive conduct”. full story available on the guradian website. they are catching up. i'm still going to take legal action against them. we'll settle free advertising and coverage and a key out 
but yes this is what they found, thos what i'm taking to court! wide open. some say, others do.

schedule: mark your calendars for the next dates/times for class, workshops and events! 
tuesdays: on-going open community class. the glove @theglovebk. 6:30-8:30pm. kundalini yoga warm-up 6:30-7 followed by capoeira angola 7-8:30pm. sliding scale $8-15. discount class pass for eligible poc/qtpoc. 
saturday: 11/17. adrian miles @gods401kplan will be giving an open level /age capoeira angola workshop. music and movement. sweetwater yoga & dance, bronx. sliding scale $8-20. 
dia de la concencia negra: 11/20. intensive capoeira music workshop. the glove @theglovebk. 6:30-8:30pm. sliding scale. $10-20. students may use class pass if it is up to date.
#metoo in the roda: 12/16. invite only. closed discussion on safety, healing and transformation. flyer will be posted with info. must rsvp to receive coordinates.
please wear uniform for all classes and workshops if you have one. if not. black pants with a belt, tee shirt with sleeves that can be tucked in and sneakers. 
jogo bonito tees and dobraos for sale $20 each. get yours to support the vision. all proceeds go to our community projects. link in bio for details. 
anything else, holla!

text:
it’s a great day today. this is another piece from one of the (9 in all) part of windows to my soul. this installation is big, it takes up a large room. i started 3 1/2 years before working on faith that it would find where it must go. anyone with ideas please help. the piece in total is about child abuse all abuse and trauma.  how to give birth to yourself and the journey to love yourself.  because then we can open our hearts and love others. it was my life, but it is so many other lives out there. i know that , i hear them.
.
.
,
.

text:
preámbulo. 
jodido día a día.

apago la luz y me escondo en la esquina de esta habitación. 
luego lloro, 
porque sé que sólo soy jodidas partes rotas.

me levanto y cojo mi guitarra, porque sus cuerdas son cicatrices,
como yo, y aún siguen riendo, 
tú sigues doliendo.

no debería ser fácil escribir esto, pero me has hecho sentir tan poco,
que lo único que me sale es apagar mis emociones,
y me dedico a pensar en escalas de gris.

capítulo...
jodido juicio final.

y oye, sabes que no puedes culparme por atreverme a decir al fin mi verdad,
que no cierta para ti y quizá inestable para tanta otra gente.
¿pero quién se atrevería a pensar que apagas a tu mujer?

luego te arrodillas, buscando redención, pidiendo su perdón.
ingenuo ahora tú, si crees que puedes calmar tu conciencia y limpiar tu alma
con cuatro palabras vacías.

agradecimientos.
jodida (¿bendita?) muerte.

ambos con marcas imborrables bajo la piel, unas bajo el producto del pecado, 
otras bajo el desamparo de gente que enmudece cuando escucha esta verdad,
y sólo llora cuando dejo de llorar para siempre.

tú, que seguirás con tu vida en ese ático a cincuenta metros de altura.
yo, que seré recordada a tres metros bajo tierra. unas veces como víctima y otras porque me lo busqué. 
tú, que vivirás siendo un cobarde.
y mientras yo, morí sabiendo que lo único que quería era vivir.

in october, i also had a photo session with  @cbtrn  also on long island. the only thing i did it was to warn him in our conversation that i would be in thong and come with my husband. because by nature i am a very suspicious person and therefore assumed that something might go wrong. but i am lucky and he did not bother me, because i initially put him in such a framework and he agreed! if he told me to come alone, then i refused to!!! because it is a red flag 🚩 
i am very sorry that this happened to the girls! and from his side it is not professionally and disgustingly! i also want the girls be less trusting and stipulate the boundaries at the stage of the contract! this is really the case when so many people say the same thing and this cannot be a lie!!! i hope many people have drawn their own conclusions from this situation!!! i'm already suspicious, but now i trust people even less because of such cases! :
:
sorry cristian, but i do not want to be an advertisement for a person who doesn’t know well and who, as it turned out, offended others girls!!!
:
:

text:
rita levi-montalcini, (22 april 1909 – 30 december 2012) was an italian nobel laureate, honored for her work in neurobiology.
she was awarded the 1986 nobel prize in physiology or medicine jointly with colleague stanley cohen for the discovery of nerve growth factor (ngf).
from 2001 until her death, she also served in the italian senate as a senator for life.
on 22 april 2009, she became the first nobel laureate ever to reach the age of 100, and the event was feted with a party at rome's city hall.
during world war ii she set up a laboratory in her bedroom and studied the growth of nerve fibers in chicken embryos, which laid the groundwork for much of her later research.

rita levi-montalcini, (22 april 1909 – 30 december 2012) was an italian nobel laureate, honored for her work in neurobiology.
she was awarded the 1986 nobel prize in physiology or medicine jointly with colleague stanley cohen for the discovery of nerve growth factor (ngf).
from 2001 until her death, she also served in the italian senate as a senator for life.
on 22 april 2009, she became the first nobel laureate ever to reach the age of 100, and the event was feted with a party at rome's city hall.
during world war ii she set up a laboratory in her bedroom and studied the growth of nerve fibers in chicken embryos, which laid the groundwork for much of her later research.

text: as a parent, when someone has hurt your child, often your first inclination is to harm the person who harmed them. and, while this is a completely normal response especially in the case of child sexual abuse, we encourage you to stop and think first. keep in mind that your child may very well feel like they are to blame for the harm that person experiences, regardless of how well deserved it might be and how well intentioned you feel about it. they may also still love the person but hate their actions, and yet they still don't want to see the person hurt. additionally, the consequences that you may face as a result of your actions is an additional burden your child will feel as well as the potential absence of your presence if you are convicted of a crime. all of these possibilities can add to your child's trauma. trust us, we get it! but, please just stop and think first.  #childsexabuseawareness #stopchildsexabuse #childsexabusesurvivor #parentsofchilldsexabusesurvivor #sexualassault #endchildsexabuse #endrapeculture #childabuse #sextrafficking #atlanta #atl #georgia #women #girls #teens #awareness #sexcrimes #rapevictims #rape #victims #children #prevention #trafficking  #survivor #tips #blogger #speaker #metoo #advocate

text:
frauenbilder nach männer-drehbuch
über die emanzipation der frau als männerphantasie

essay von christoph may erschienen im auslöser #2/2018

auszug

als männerforscher schreibe ich nicht über frauen. und auch als mann vermeide ich es, über frauen zu sprechen. was wissen wir schon? nach #metoo ist klar: wir wissen nichts! weder wie sich frauen fühlen, noch welche probleme sie haben. bevor wir nicht unsere eigene rolle und unsere privilegien als weiße, westliche männer hinterfragen, dürfen wir uns kein urteil erlauben. “ich weiß, wie die frauen ticken!“ war schon immer eine schamlose lüge. das gebot der stunde: nicht über, sondern mit den frauen sprechen. das gilt für ärzte, therapeuten und lehrer genauso wie für berater, unternehmer und filmschaffende. für kritische männerforscher gilt es erst recht.

mein spezialgebiet ist die enorme phantasielosigkeit von männerphantasien in filmen und serien. es beginnt schon beim personal: superheroes, ex-bullen, killer-maschinen und um sich schlagende testosteron-prügel. allesamt formen der aushärtung des männlichen körperpanzers. vom man of steel über iron man bis zu hulk, dem alten froschkönig. die innenschau ist nicht weniger geistlos: zombies, mutanten, monster und aliens verhandeln das kreatürliche innere moderner männlichkeit. emotionale sprachlosigkeit wird hier als gewebewucherung inszeniert oder als krüppeltier. von gollum aus herr der ringe über die weißen wanderer in game of thrones bis zum xenomorph.

und drittens die hypermaskuline psychogeographie. archaische innenwelten und gefühls-steppen soweit das auge reicht: von westeros bis westworld, durch mittelerde bis nach gotham city, von hogwarts direkt in die oasis. in meiner forschung zeige ich, dass es sich bei all diesen körperpanzern, kreaturen und psychogeographien um spezifisch männliche darstellungsformen handelt.

stop_filter_tweet: frauenbilder nach männer-drehbuch über die emanzipation der frau als männerphantasie essay von christoph may erschienen im auslöser /2018 auszug als männerforscher schreibe ich nicht über frauen . und auch als mann vermeide ich es , über frauen zu sprechen . wissen wir schon ? nach ist klar : wir wissen nichts ! weder wie sich frauen fühlen , noch welche probleme sie haben . bevor wir nicht unsere eigene rolle und unsere privilegien als weiße , westliche männer hinterfragen , dürfen wir uns kein ueil erlauben . “ ich weiß , wie die frauen ticken ! “ war schon immer eine schamlose lüge . das gebot der stunde : nicht über , sondern mit den frauen sprechen . das gilt für ärzte , therapeuten und lehrer genauso wie für berater , unternehmer und filmschaffende . für kritische männerforscher gilt es erst recht . mein spezialgebiet ist die enorme phantasielosigkeit von männerphantasien filmen und serien . es beginnt schon beim personal : superheroes , ex-bullen , killer-maschinen und um sich schlagende testosteron-prügel . allesamt formen der aushäung des männlichen körperpanzers . vom man steel über iron man bis zu hulk , dem alten froschkönig . die innenschau ist nicht weniger geistlos : zombies , mutanten , monster und aliens verhandeln das kreatürliche innere moderner männlichkeit . emotionale sprachlosigkeit wird hier als gewebewucherung inszenie oder als krüppeltier . von gollum aus herr der ringe über die weißen wanderer game thrones bis zum xenomorph . und drittens die hypermaskuline psychogeographie . archaische innenwelten und gefühls-steppen soweit das auge reicht : von westeros bis westworld , durch mittelerde bis nach gotham city , von hogwas direkt die oasis . meiner forschung zeige ich , dass es sich bei diesen körperpanzern , kreaturen und psychogeographien um spezifisch männliche darstellungsformen handelt . . . . read mensstudies.eu uslöser

text: wie ich gerade gelesen habe, wurde gestern gefeiert, dass die frau seit 100 jahren das wahlrecht hat. ich verstehe nicht, weshalb das ein grund zu feiern ist. das sollte normal sein. feiern sollte man lieber, dass seit 100 jahren aggressive alphamänner egotechnisch am arsch sind, weil sie einsehen mussten und zum teil heute noch einsehen müssen, dass frauen genau so viel wert sind wie männer. und was rechte und gesetze angeht: "nein" heißt halt doch immernoch "mhh na jaa nee... oder ja, vielleicht, doch" und eben nicht "nein". und schlaf ist zwar keine zustimmung, aber eben auch keine ablehnung. erst recht nicht gespielter schlaf aus angst... nach drei "neins ('nein", "ich möchte das nicht", "ich möchte schlafen, mir geht es auch nicht gut"), einem gegenseitigen "gute nacht" und einer viertel stunde schockstarre kann einem täter einfach nicht zu 100 prozent klar sein, dass das opfer nicht an sex interessiert ist... das ist unmöglich festzustellen, schließlich hätte es nach dem 500. nein auch noch ein 501. mal "nein" sagen können. gestern in gera. also fickt euch einfach. aber bitte euch selbst. text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
powher day 2:: nine years is how long i’ve known natalie. we were instant friends, brought together abroad with a common love for pasta, wine & gelato. in nine years we’ve shared many laughs, inside jokes, and professional advice. she is strikingly beautiful, hilarious, and insanely talented when it comes to graphic design, diy & photography (to name a few). but i think i’m most proud of the strength she showed during a life-changing event: sharing with the world that she was a victim of sexual assault. instead of being a victim, though, she became a survivor and is on a mission to help other survivors thrive. check out her charity @thearmyofsurvivors .
.
.

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
@regran_ed from @belinda_vegan -  babe's true story
have you heard about sham chewing ( chewing nothing)? due to the deprived environment that these intelligent, sensitive,animals are confined in they will develop neurotic coping behaviors such as bar biting, sham chewing, and obsessively pressing on water bottles. the confinement is so intense that the pigs sometimes even attack their crates.
_
after visiting several pig factory farms, investigator lauren omelas wrote, "what will remain with me forever is the sound of desperate pigs banging their heads against immovable door and their constant and repeated biting at the prison bars that held him captive. this, i know now, is a sign of mental collapse. what has happened to the human race that it can close its eyes to all this suffering?
_
mother pigs, spend most of their lives in individual "gestation crates", which are approximately 7 ft long and 2 ft wide - too small for them to even turn around. just before giving birth, they are moved to a "farrowing" crates, which are wide enough for them to lie down and nurse their babies but still not large enough for them to turn around or build nests for their young. it would be like you spending your life in a coffin. a pregnant pigs biological need to build a nest before having her babies is so great that some pigs confined in modern hog buildings will rub their snouts raw on the concrete floor, while trying to satisfy the drive.
_
please open your eyes! you're 5 minutes worth of taste (bacon) is a lifetime worth of suffering and death for them! when will you say enough is enough? when will you stop participating in this violence system of oppression, abuse, suffering, and their ultimate death? you can not only survive but thrive on a plant-based diet.
embrace veganism!🌱

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
“in speaking up i got my power back. i know my truth and no one can ever tell me that i am not a reliable narrator of my own experience.“ - model, author, activist #padmalakshmi spoke at the #glamourwoty awards about being raped at 16. for decades she kept the horrific experience to herself
.
.
.
in a 2018 nyt opinion piece, padma explained why she and many women choose to stay silent:
“when i think about it now, i realize that by the time of this rape, i had already absorbed certain lessons. when i was 7 years old, my stepfather’s relative touched me between my legs and put my hand on his erect penis. shortly after i told my mother and stepfather, they sent me to india for a year to live with my grandparents. the lesson was: if you speak up, you will be cast out.
these experiences have affected me and my ability to trust. it took me decades to talk about this with intimate partners and a therapist.
some say a man shouldn’t pay a price for an act he committed as a teenager. but the woman pays the price for the rest of her life, and so do the people who love her.” #metoo #believewomen

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
**trigger** 📙lit appreciation:
not that bad by roxane gay / @roxanegay74
.
.
i'm still reading this one. and i'm so glad it's been written. it's not just because this topic is now relevant in society (despite it being prevalent since the dawn of humans) but to have a narrative that speaks honestly about the brutality and normalisation of rape culture from those who have experienced its reality- is both needed and appreciated. it's not unique in its context, but it poses the right questions. .
.
candid but painful memoirs mixed with thoughtful perspectives and straight-talking ideas on how to engage with breaking down this destructive disillusioned virus-infused way of thinking and acting. .
.
some amazing talking points so if anyone wants to discuss.. holla 🙋🏾‍♀️
.
.
another thumbs up for roxane gay 👍🏽🙌🏽

sentir la llamada del feminismo es una de las cosas más bonitas que me han pasado jamás. estoy aprendiendo aún a entender muchas cosas y a desprogramar otras que tengo demasiado interiorizadas. aprender a no juzgarnos, a apoyarnos, a creer en la fuerza revolucionaria que tenemos las mujeres, y solo las mujeres, para parar esta crisis de valores, de creencias, esta rabia contra el otro que amenaza a europa y al mundo. también despertar y darnos cuenta que el feminismo no solo es blanco, universitario, de países desarrollados. estamos todas en el mismo barco porque si nos tocan a una, nos tocan a todas y a cada uno de los derechos, logros y sufrimiento arrancado .
.
estoy preparada para el #8m, la huelga y todo lo que surja. y tú? 💜 .
.

text:
selfies con mujeres berracas. la documentalista carmen oquendo-villar, una puertoriqueña que conoce bogotá mejor que muchos bogotanos. su documental (en proceso), diana de santa fe nos permite tener una mirada cercana a la realidad de una líder comunitaria que trabaja en pro de la población trans en la localidad de santa fe en bogotá. conocerla y escucharla en persona ha sido una de esas experiencias transformadoras. su trabajo, su pasión alientan a cualquiera para trabajar por lo que se debe. como dicen en inglés “carmen is doing the right thing right”. .

text_retweet:
proud to announce intrusion has its uk premiere 🇬🇧 this saturday 17th november at underwire film festival in the curated programme of short films, “art in the time of #metoo”. .

saturday 17th november - 8.30pm
rich mix, 35-47 bethnal green rd, london . . “i wrote and shot intrusion a little under two years prior to the #metoo movement’s explosion into the mainstream. when sexual assault, sexual harassment and coercion in and around the workplace was discussed privately amongst women, but before a wave of collective power allowed us to begin to speak publicly with more chance of a recourse to justice. 
it’s critical to point out that while this revolution is something of a cleansing fire, there is still a huge amount of violence and harassment being perpetuated behind the scenes. kept quiet. hushed up. men are still behaving badly. women are still being silenced.” ~ from @mingzhuhii’s director’s statement 2018 .

text:
30th november is celebrated as south asian women’s day for peace, democracy, justice and human rights. on this day, civil society organizations across the region organize events to celebrate sisterhood, solidarity and address common concerns of conflicts, violence in the region. 
sexual harassment against women is rampant in these regions and sexual harassment is often normalised as part of daily occurrences women face at work and at public spaces. the arrival of the #me too movement in india has provided women a platform to express themselves and share stories of abuse and violence they have faced while studying or working at different institutions. 
the #me too movement is very powerful and is sending a clear message to the society that sexual harassment is unacceptable. it is also asking men to recognise that some of their own behaviour patterns are unacceptable and they are often crossing boundaries and not seeking consent! 
in this social context, we are trying to organise programmes across bangladesh, nepal, india, sri lanka and pakistan that touch upon this issue. 
in kolkata, swayam is organising “#metoo and south asia: film screening & panel discussion” on 30th november at rotary sadan in the evening. the programme will help generate a discussion based on short films/documentaries on sexual harassment from the different regions and how this impacts women. the panelist will generate a discussion on sexual harassment, its impact, the #me too movement, what it means for women’s rights, pros/cons, and its impact in different south asian countries. 
we aim to create a platform for sharing, solidarity and planning ways forward. 
venue: rotary sadan 
timing: 4 to 7pm
name: Dhruva/ধ্রুব/ध्रुव

text:
i am so incredibly proud to have collaborated with the legendary @missalyssakitt with this sexy pinup logo to represent her new writing venture, with which she will continue to empower and inspire all women. this has been a while in the making and we are so excited to bring this sassy lady to you today! please read alyssa’s story below, i hope you will tune in! ❤️
・・・
2018 has been a huge year of personal growth for me. it was exactly one year ago that i reached rock bottom due to substance abuse, trauma therapy, anxiety that was cracking me in two and over-committing myself to a degree that i could barely keep going. i began writing in a little gold journal. small short stories first, creative non-fiction, then a torrent began to stream out of me of things that i’d been holding in for decades. things with seriously dark undertones as to how i have come to be the way i am. 
over this year i’ve felt myself grow stronger through sharing with you all and heard the incredible stories of some seriously strong women around me. it is through conversation that these dark commonalities come to light. in the age of #metoo and the dawn of new age of feminism and speaking out, i felt more and more aligned with what began as a simple burlesque moniker. i’m really excited to be launching my new blog in 2019. 
feminist fatale will include my own research, writing, interviews and opinion pieces from everything from burlesque, the body positive movement and the strong women who shape and influence us every day.

this new logo is designed by the amazing @justcallmecatdesign - who has patiently collaborated with me after i approached her four years ago with this concept!
•
#feministart #feministwriting #feministfatale #feminism #femmefatale #speakingout #strongwomen #pinupartist #pinupillustration #blacklatex #redheadgirl #burlesquequeen #missalyssakitt #justcallmecatdesign

you are beautifully rich in your own flavour and you shouldn’t have to sacrifice this for the sake of anyone else.

take this quote for instance.. ‘she had blue skin, 
and so did he, 
he kept it hid,
and so did she,

they searched for blue, 
their whole life through, 
then passed right by,
and never knew.’ 🌄💗🌄💗🌄 .
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

привет, друзья!
сегодня в 13 часов начнутся 8 лунные сутки. символ дня - птица феникс.
⠀
это день преобразований, кардинальных изменений, внутренней трансформации.  сегодня весь ваш организм перестраивается. происходят невидимые для вас изменения на биохимическом уровне, на уровне клеток и тканей. организм насыщается энергией. это ваш шанс начать жизнь, как люди любят говорить, «с чистого листа».
.
день удачен для любого рода преобразований. можно взяться за новые дела, наметить новые планы, сделать дома ремонт, отправиться в путешествие, переехать в другую квартиру, сменить место работы. и, конечно же, не забывать о внутренней, духовной трансформации. заниматься самоанализом, самоочищением, просить прощения у людей и прощать их самих. постарайтесь также запомнить свои сны. в этот день сны раскрывают нам смысл жизни, рассказывают о нашей миссии, для чего мы прибыли на землю и какая роль в жизни мира нам уготована.

text: "...a pasi nyíltan kimondta, hogy szerinte túl erős akaratú vagyok, ezért be kell törni, meg egyébként is, ne beszéljek már olyan hülyeségről, mint a feminizmus. az álláspontját többször hangoztatta, szerinte ahhoz, hogy valaki kedve szerint használható legyen, annak érdekében a személyiséget az alapokig le kell rombolni, hogy aztán a saját képére újra formálva függővé tehesse. szerencsémre eléggé hülyén csinálta és volt olyan ostoba, hogy nyílt lapokkal játsszon, így végül is megkönnyítette a dolgomat és elhagytam. ebben az időszakban készült a „senkinek sem kell kellenie” képpár, ami – az emberi szívhez állítólag leginkább rokon - disznó szívet ábrázol. a szív gúzsba kötött, ezzel jelképezve, hogy beragadtam a szituációba, nem tudok mozdulni se előre, se hátra. a kép párján a szív már nincs jelen, „kiszabadult”, de a fenyegetően meredező kötelek jelképezik az attól való félelmet, hogy a pasi „megtört férfiasságáért” bosszút akar majd állni.” ——- ‘…the guy put bluntly that he thinks that i’m too headstrong, so he has to break me, and anyway, i shouldn’t talk about such stupid things like feminism. he repeatedly shared his views on to have someone useful for him, her personality should be demolished up to the basics and then he can change it so that she will depend on him. luckily, he was stupid enough to do these things explicitly and he played it open so he made it easier for me and i left him. this set of pictures, titled: ‘no one needs to be wanted’, depict a pig heart which anatomy is the most similar to the ones of humans. the heart is bound which symbolizes that i was stuck in a situation and could not move neither forward, nor backward. the heart is no longer visible on the second picture, it’s free, but the rampant ropes symbolize the fear that this man may want to take revenge for his ‘broken masculinity’. #nane #vankepemhozza #domesticviolence  #metoo #getthepicture

text:
when your heart is completely broken because your friend died and you found out from her son, and now both his parents are dead and you feel completely helpless. 
when you want to be strong and be there for your friend, but they don't want you to have any concern for them.

when you are sitting at home crying your eyes out alone on beautiful sunday, and you can't breathe anymore.

when you feel completely alone because everyone keeps leaving for other priorities, and nobody cares about you.

when people around you are so self absorbed that they can't recognize anything anymore.

when people around you are so privileged with the ability to block things out or nullify their feelings that they want to force you into a jaded non-binary stance.

when you feel like you are being forced to forfeit your own sanity because everyone around you wants you to have a meaningless mindless stupid smile on your face like an ugly clown.

when you can't breathe anymore because you are crying so hard your nose is clogged up and runny.

when strangers try to take advantage of you because you wear your heart on your sleeve.

when your heart starts bleeding and nobody stands up to help try and stop it.

when you feel like your heart is going to stop because you can't believe it's really that bad.

when you try to calm yourself down so your heart stops racing.

when you have to take deep breaths and remember to exhale so that you can regain your focus.

when you wipe your tears away and finally get up.

when you cried so much you feel completely drained and need a glass of water.

when you get up and think about the steps towards self care and your own well being.

when you remember that everyone has bad days and every has good days, however when and few or far between.

when you remember that you are beautiful and have a beautiful life and have everything to be thankful for.

when your nose clears.
when you run of of tears.
when you conquer your fears.
you remember...
you remind yourself that you are worthy.
you remember..
that you are able bodied and capable.
you remember..
you can do anything you put your mind to.
you remember
that you are your own person and healer.
#modelvolunteer

شیوا:
بە بۆنەی نیزێک بوونەوە لە 25یnov ڕۆژی بەرەنگاری توندوتێژی دژی ژنان و پشتیوانی لە هەشتەگی #بێدەنگی_بشکێنین ، لەژێر هەشتەگی #منیش #metoo " باس داکەم زۆربە یا هەموومان جارێکیش بووبێت ئەزمونمان کردوە.

من کە خەڵکی وڵاتێکم کە ئیسلام تێیدا حکومەت دەکات و لە ماڵێ و لە مەدرەسە و شەقام و کۆڵان و... لە هەموو شوێنێک بە کردەوە هەوڵیان داوە ڕەگەزی بەرانبەرمان لێ بکەن بە دێو و درنج و بیسەلمێنن کە هەموو پیاوێک ئێمەی بۆ گان دەوێت و هەر ژنێکی کراوە و کۆمەڵایەتی سۆزانییەکی بێ ئەخلاقە. ژنی بەحەدەب ئەوەیە جەستەی ڕووتی بەدەرەوە نەبێت و کەمتر لەگەڵ نێرینان "بتریقێتەوە". کوڕی باشیش ئەوانە بوون کە...! کوڕی باش؟! لە ڕاستی دا هەموو پیاوان کوڕی باش بوون ئەگەر ئێمەی "بێ ئەخلاق" لە ڕێگەمان بەدەر نەکردبان!
پێم وابوو تەنیا پیاوانێک کە لەوەها کۆمەڵگاگەلێک و لەژێر پەروەردەی هاوشێوەیەی ئەوەی ئێمەوە گەورە بووبێتن ئەوەندە سێکسیست و دەستدرێژیکەر فێر دەبن. بەڵام لە ڕاستی دا ژن کە بووی ژیان ئەزموونگەلێکی زۆرت دەخاتە بەر دەم. -دەسترێژی لە ڕێگای دەست بۆ هێنان

ئەوەیانم دوو جار بۆ پێش هاتووە. 
یەکەم جار:
 دوازدە ساڵ بووم، بەدەر لە کاتی مەدرەسە کلاسی تریش دەچووم. لە ماڵەوە زۆر دوور نەبوو بەڵام کۆڵان بە کۆڵان بوو. لە ڕێگای چوونە کلاس هەر ئەوەندە دەنگی ماتۆڕ سوارێکم بیست، هەر لەگەڵکو بڵێی یەک_دوو گەیشتە ڕاستی من و دەستێک کە وە سمتم کەوت. 
مهاباد شارێکی چکۆلەیە، گەڕەکی وایە لە بێدەنگیان پەپووی لێ دەخوێنێت.. ئەوەندە چۆڵە کە پێت وایە کەسی لێ ناژیێت، وابزانم تەبیعییە لەو شەرایتە دا هاواری یارمەتیش نەکەی و لەترسانیش زمانت لاڵ بێت! ئەوە تەنیا ترس و قینە بە ڕەگەزی بەرانبەر کە سەراسەر داتگرێت و تەواوی ئێسقانەکانت وەک زنجیری لێک پساو لەسەریەک خۆنەگرن و تا ئاستی بەربوونەوە لەسەر چۆکت بلەرزی و ئیتر هەرگیز ئەو کۆڵانانە بۆ گەیشتن بە مەقسەد نەگرییەوە بەر.
زۆری پێ دەچێت هەتا ئەو ترس و قینەی کە نەخۆشێکی ڕەوانی لە دەرونتی دا دروست کردوە ببێتەوە بە وێنەیەکی پاک و بێگەرد و بێتاوان لەو پیاوانەش کە هەمیشە پشتیان گرتووی. کاتێک چاو لە چاوی باوکت، براکەت و خزمەکانت دەکەی هەزار جار لە خۆت دەپرسی: ئەوانە دەستیان بۆ چەند کەسدرێژ کردووە؟! لە یەکەم چرکە بە دواوە چاوەڕوانم دەکرد و ڕەنگە هیواشم خواستبێت خۆزگە دووبارە بێتەوە و ئەوجارەیان حیسابی بخەمە بەر دەستی.
#نووسەری_ئاماتۆڕ #بۆ_من_ڕووی_داوە_بۆ_تۆ_چی #thefutureisfemale #بێدەنگی_بشکێنین

کوڕی باش؟ ! لە ڕاستی دا هەموو پیاوان کوڕی باش بوون ئەگەر ئێمەی `` بێ ئەخلاق `` لە ڕێگەمان بەدەر نەکردبان ! پێم وابوو تەنیا پیاوانێک کە لەوەها کۆمەڵگاگەلێک و لەژێر پەروەردەی هاوشێوەیەی ئەوەی ئێمەوە گەورە بووبێتن ئەوەندە سێکسیست و دەستدرێژیکەر فێر دەبن . بەڵام لە ڕاستی دا ژن کە بووی ژیان ئەزموونگەلێکی زۆرت دەخاتە بەر دەم . -دەسترێژی لە ڕێگای دەست بۆ هێنان ئەوەیانم دوو جار بۆ پێش هاتووە . یەکەم جار : دوازدە ساڵ بووم، بەدەر لە کاتی مەدرەسە کلاسی تریش دەچووم . لە ماڵەوە زۆر دوور نەبوو بەڵام کۆڵان بە کۆڵان بوو . لە ڕێگای چوونە کلاس هەر ئەوەندە دەنگی ماتۆڕ سوارێکم بیست، هەر لەگەڵکو بڵێی یەک_دوو گەیشتە ڕاستی من و دەستێک کە وە سمتم کەوت . مهاباد شارێکی چکۆلەیە، گەڕەکی وایە لە بێدەنگیان پەپووی لێ دەخوێنێت.. ئەوەندە چۆڵە کە پێت وایە کەسی لێ ناژیێت، وابزانم تەبیعییە لەو شەرایتە دا هاواری یارمەتیش نەکەی و لەترسانیش زمانت لاڵ بێت ! ئەوە تەنیا ترس و قینە بە ڕەگەزی بەرانبەر کە سەراسەر داتگرێت و تەواوی ئێسقانەکانت وەک زنجیری لێک پساو لەسەریەک خۆنەگرن و تا ئاستی بەربوونەوە لەسەر چۆکت بلەرزی و ئیتر هەرگیز ئەو کۆڵانانە بۆ گەیشتن بە مەقسەد نەگرییەوە بەر . زۆری پێ دەچێت هەتا ئەو ترس و قینەی کە نەخۆشێکی ڕەوانی لە دەرونتی دا دروست کردوە ببێتەوە بە وێنەیەکی پاک و بێگەرد و بێتاوان لەو پیاوانەش کە هەمیشە پشتیان گرتووی . کاتێک چاو لە چاوی باوکت، براکەت و خزمەکانت دەکەی هەزار جار لە خۆت دەپرسی : ئەوانە دەستیان بۆ چەند کەسدرێژ کردووە؟ ! لە یەکەم چرکە بە دواوە چاوەڕوانم دەکرد و ڕەنگە هیواشم خواستبێت خۆزگە دووبارە بێتەوە و ئەوجارەیان حیسابی بخەمە بەر دەستی . ێدەنگی_بشکێنین ☟☟☟☟☟

‘ “is it a problem that i love you?” in his hysteric attacks he smashed the door, the cupboard, the phone, the eyeglasses…sometimes he even scratched and rinsed the skin on his face leaving major scars. then, facing the outside world, he blamed me for it. this has become a routine. at home, a raging neurotic or an over-amorous suitor holding me in the hollow of his hand. of course, i am ungrateful, everything is my fault, nothing is good enough for me, i don’t know what i want, i am a horrible mother and spouse, i ruin everything and everyone around me. he is complaining to everyone. he belittles me not just at home but at every turn. for the outside world, i am an ungrateful, lunatic woman who clearly has some issues. i wanted to leave him multiple times. the result was a ferocious attack, suicide threats, making a scene involving as many people as he could. last time he even involved the police claiming that i want to kidnap his child. even his mother joined my mortification. they did everything to turn my kids against me telling them what kind of a mother i am who wants to leave him. i’m afraid of him. i feel disgusted. he is flirting with other women in front of me and humiliates me in public. then he hugs me, because he loves me. “is this your problem - that i love you?” see the hungarian version below. ——————————- ——lásd magyar szöveggel lejjebb!!!!

text:
i really like this picture because it's so true. 
i'm tired of putting on a brave face. i hate faking a smile. but i do it anyway. because i just want to avoid the question "what's wrong with you?". sometimes even i don't know what's wrong with me, i just get sad without a reason. or i'm sad because of what happened to me so i'm never able to answer that question.
the bravest thing i did this year was opening up to friends. i was always afraid to open up to someone. i was afraid people would judge me. i was afraid people would laugh at me. i was afraid they don't want to be friends with me anymore. i was just afraid they would see me as a different person.
i opened up to friends via whatsapp and i even opened up to a friend in person which was even harder to do, but all of them reacted so sweet. 
it really felt good and i am proud of myself for doing it.
.
.

text:
2018 has been a huge year of personal growth for me. it was exactly one year ago that i reached rock bottom due to substance abuse, trauma therapy, anxiety that was cracking me in two and over-committing myself to a degree that i could barely keep going. i began writing in a little gold journal. small short stories first, creative non-fiction, then a torrent began to stream out of me of things that i’d been holding in for decades. things with seriously dark undertones as to how i have come to be the way i am. 
over this year i’ve felt myself grow stronger through sharing with you all and heard the incredible stories of some seriously strong women around me. it is through conversation that these dark commonalities come to light. in the age of #metoo and the dawn of new age of feminism and speaking out, i felt more and more aligned with what began as a simple burlesque moniker. i’m really excited to be launching my new blog in 2019. 
feminist fatale will include my own research, writing, interviews and opinion pieces from everything from burlesque, the body positive movement and the strong women who shape and influence us every day.

this new logo is designed by the amazing @justcallmecatdesign - who has patiently collaborated with me after i approached her four years ago with this concept!

text: «дорогу осилит идущий»- с детства слышала эту фразу от мамы и от бабушки. начала понимать только годам к 35. актуально и сейчас😉  за последние два месяца я несколько раз слышала фразу от продакшенов: «мы не хотим женщину режиссера». в этой фразе все прекрасно. я часто слышу это-потому что я режиссер и потому что я женщина😜 и всегда в моем мозгу происходит коллапс и разрыв шаблонов. в смысле? не по профессиональному, а по половому признаку берете на работу? а мужчина режиссер-это «знак качества»? и сразу вспоминаю чудовищные ситуации, когда я брала проект в безнадежном состоянии и снимала за уволенного режиссера другого пола. это катастрофа, что до сих пор существуют продюсеры, которые считают, что режиссура (и еще, видимо, тонна профессий) не женское дело. у профессии нет пола, есть талант и профессионализм. есть прекрасные режиссеры мужчины и прекрасные режиссеры женщины. есть профнепригодные и те, и другие. я за профессиональный подход✊🏼#женщинарежиссер#раддановикова#womeninmotion#womandirector#filmmaking#femalefilmmaker#metoo#filmdirector#nosexism

text:
warum haben wir sex, wenn wir es gar nicht so richtig wollen?
~
über diese frage habe ich mich angeregt mit ben, nicht auf @benscouch , sondern auf meiner couch, unterhalten.
und heißt es eigentlich immer, wenn wir jemanden zu uns nach hause einladen und dann auch noch küssen, dass wir dann auf jeden fall sex mit ihm / ihr haben wollen? „geheimcode“ für netflix & chill 😉.
~
sexuelle belästigung und warum grenzen setzen so wichtig ist, konnten wir bei der thematik auch nicht ganz außen vor lassen. und nur weil ich feucht bin, heißt das nicht, dass ich auch sex möchte.
~
wir haben also einen ziemlich großen bogen geschlagen und es ist ein tolles podcastinterview geworden 😊❤️.
den link dazu packe ich dir in meine bio!
~
und wie hat ben unser gespräch wundervoll zusammengefasst? “fuck me, but ask me first.” 🔥
~
ich freue mich sehr auf eure diskussion darüber. hattet ihr schon mal sex, obwohl ihr dachtet, “mmh, das braucht’s jetzt eigentlich nicht?” und warum habt ihr es trotzdem gemacht?
~

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

text:
#しなくていいがまん 
旅のお礼を伝えにいつもの神社へ

行きたかったカフェをやめて
近くのお菓子屋さんでケーキを買う

呼ばれた気がしてたまたま寄った神社が熊本地震で壊れてしまっていて
募金を募ってたけど
お金が無さすぎてせめてもと
200円賽銭箱に入れる

喉が渇いたからと
水を買うために寄ったイオンで
ついつい本屋に立ち寄り

小林麻耶ちゃんの本をチラ読みしたら
おー
metoo
と思えたので即買い

残金500円のお財布の中

それでも良い買い物をしたな❤️ インスタのタグ付けを敢えてします。
本を売るためだけではなく
同じように悩む人に
伝えたいのだろうと
そう思ったので。

生まれついて
前向きに生きれる人とは違って
苦しみを経験して
苦しみの中で
自分を省みて
変わろうと決めて
変わっていく人は

それを周りに伝える役目をもっているのかもしれません

素直でステキな本だと思いました

同世代❤️(今年は32歳の予定だけど)

わたしも
病気で苦しんだことがあるからこそ
同感するところもあり
そして

自分と見つめ合い

我慢しない
自分をもっと愛する
と
決めて進んだこの一年を
この本を読みながら
復習した気分になりました

#metoo
#女性の生き方
#もっと楽しんでもっと楽チンでいい
#今日の空は今日だけ
#直感で選ぶ日々
#柿のケーキ#モンブラン
#草刈りする人と空
初版印刷日がわたしの誕生日❤️これも運命

text:
high fantasy
•
directed: jenna bass
starring: qondiswa james, nala khumalo, francesca varrie michel, liza scholtz
•
winner of the artistic bravery prize at the durban international film festival 2018
•
a group of young friends on a camping trip, deep in the south african countryside wake up to discover they've all swapped bodies! stranded in the wilderness, they'll have to navigate a personal-political labyrinth if their friendships and their lives are ever to be the same again.
•
it’s a timely film when viewed through the lens of broader global movements like black lives matter and #metoo, although bass says the  movie is firmly rooted in the “observable daily reality” of south african society. “if you live in south africa, these things hit you very hard on a daily basis,” she says.
•
"high fantasy's unassuming, yet piercing examination of race, class and gender embeds bass firmly in the pantheon of an exciting new wave of south african filmmaking characterized by introspective directors who are digging deep.” shadow and act
•
"with a raw style that’s part ‘blair witch’ and part ‘tangerine’, the film probes apartheid’s unhealed wounds, and challenges the platitudes of a promised peaceful future." tiff
•
"high fantasy" is a movie for the woke set in 2017; it's about the exploration of the beliefs we espouse on the surface, art that bores beneath that surface to mine its characters' true feelings. it's therefore uncomfortable to watch, but that's natural.” the playlist
•
"surprising and challenging"  cinema axis
•
"the strength of the film is that it's willing to push past the homilies we've all been taught about diversity and cooperation and focus on the messy politics and human feelings underneath.” popmatters
•
opens friday 16 nov
book at webtickets (available at pick n pay)
•

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
the media society: gal-dem – women of colour in the media.

they are the #blackbritish publishing success story of the last few years. gal-dem has gone from the twinkle in the eye of a bristol university student in 2015 to one of the foremost platforms by women of colour.

liv little, creator and editor-in-chief of gal-dem is in conversation with afua hirsch, writer, broadcaster and whose book brit(ish) has just won the blackwell’s book of the year 2018 award for non-fiction.

join us on january 7 at the university women’s club in audley square, mayfair.

@afuahirsch alt africa online, gal-dem, @livslittle #london #goingoutguide #mayfair @themediasocietyuk @uwc_london

text:
u.s. president donald trump's former aide steve bannon sought to use personal information collected online to promote "a culture war," a whistleblower christopher wiley on now-defunct political data firm cambridge analytica told u.s. senators on wednesday.

bannon, a former cambridge analytica vice president, "saw cultural warfare as a means to create enduring change in american politics," testified christopher wylie, who says information about tens of millions of facebook (fb.o) users ended up in cambridge analytica's hands.

mark hosenball
reuters
