text:
i remember getting a comment saying, 'speak like a girl', 'sit like a girl', 'eat like a girl'. i also remember a personal comment on my skin which is called racism.  prior to it, i didnt realized what it was but as i gained more knowledge i was introduced to the terms like 'racism' , 'discrimination' and 'humiliation ' which ruled the half of my innocence.
i learnt the fact that i was a widget in the hands of the adherents of satan.  i went wearing a jacket,low waist trouser with a sassy locket on my wrist and khadim sneakers , while i always inhaled the odour of insecurity around me with one eye concentrating my legs and the other peering my broad shoulders. sometimes i was judged in a crowd of four and some times covered with words in the fierce eyes ,when they strolled beside me as my 'best-friend' 'shagun bhaiya' , 'preeti yarr' and 'nalesh uncle '. there was not even a monosyllable appreciation of the way i presented myself. 
with the course of time i changed from sneakers to heels. nobody forced me to become a girl, i was adapting the ail of femininity. the racist rapist's once poped up on my screen saying 'congratulations' on my success of writing books. i was befuddled with that statements from some hooligans. i wondered how this lady-like-chic sounded now like a mother-of-pearl. 
with a blue jewel on my ring finger and with the pierced ears holding long golden rings , wearing elegance of  mekhela sador, splendid 5 inch heels, with a blonde bun, i stand here as an typical indian lady. 
and if i iook feminine i am 'thank you ' but dont misinterpret my power.  i can being a peril to your gender, my ladies and gentleman. i can slay both in saree and a jumper. *majaal hai koi isse tirchi nazaaron se dekhe, wo khud ayesi aag hai jise na ek baahaya aurat aur na hi mard ki zaat ko moksh mil sakta hai*

@carmine_inker

#instagood @poemhunter #pictureday #metoo #metoomovement #poetrycommunity #positivevibes

text:
#day316 #365daysofyogawithalisa

my yoga was this conference tonight with my friend @cassidydancer03. holy women y'all. first of all, i met @sophiabush & @reesewitherspoon. kind of. they were on stage and saw me! (i saw them.) growing up these 2 women were role models for me. i admired their ability to be themselves & then to speak up as well. they were gorgeous. i loved their kindness. i wanted red hair like sophia had on one tree hill. which i did. then i'm kinda blonde now like reese. ha!

there were so many messages tonight in all of the storytelling and conversations these women shared with us. i can't even remember them all.

the ones that stood out most to me are learning to use our voice. we've been taught to shut up, us women. even someone outspoken like me. sometimes i'm still fearful especially when posting online that someone in my family will shame me for my words. for my difference of opinion. my own belief system.

to trust my voice and not just use it. i know i'm guilty of searching for a community of approval and togetherness before i use my voice. why am i not just saying what i want vs waiting for everyone to be on my page before i say it?

to be comfortable with the uncomfortable. yoga has helped me learn this already. stop being afraid to rock the boat! be wise when doing so, but do it! you stumble thru the dark and it's awkward, it's so messy, but then you end up being the light that destroys the darkness!

i feel so inspired by all of these real women. they're famous but they're still like us. they've dealt with assault, abuse, inferiority, insecurity, unworthiness, fear.

these things are universal despite your social status or race. and we must talk about it.

if you think something is wrong, speak out against the injustice. if you don't understand, ask questions then listen. if you need to be heard, you need help- shout. scream. yell. do whatever you need to get it.

#wearethewolves stood out i think most to me. the wolves were removed from the ecosystem & everything went to shit on earth. then the wolves came back and life returned too. flowers. water. everything. women. we are the wolfpack. we have returned and we must see it. #famous

to trust my voice and not just use it. i know i am guilty of searching for a community of approval and togetherness before i use my voice. why am i not just saying what i want vs waiting for everyone to be on my page before i say it?

to be comfoable with the uncomfoable. yoga has helped me learn this already. stop being afraid to rock the boat! be wise when doing so, but do it! you stumble thru the dark and it is awkward, it is so messy, but then you end up being the light that destroys the darkness!

i feel so inspired by all of these real women. they're famous but they're still like us. they've dealt with assault, abuse, inferiority, insecurity, unwohiness, fear.

these things are universal despite your social status or race. and we must talk about it.

if you think something is wrong, speak out against the injustice. if you do not understand, ask questions then listen. if you need to be heard, you need help- shout. scream. yell. do whatever you need to get it.

 stood out i think most to me. the wolves were removed from the ecosystem & everything went to shit on eah. then the wolves came back and life returned too. flowers. water. everything. women. we are the wolfpack. we have returned and we must see it.

text: hello celestial beings and twinkles of stardust 💫a reminder that you, as a survivor, are in no way obligated to tell your story, expose the details of your assault to others, or be the face of a greater #metoo movement!! 🌈 as always, talking can help. it is cathartic & therapeutic & healing. but sometimes it can be plain exhausting & scary to feel like you have to share your story to others just because of their sheer curiosity, or because they’re making you up to be a symbol of something greater, something you can’t necessarily control. 🦋 the beauty of healing from abuse & assault is taking steps to feel back in control of your life. and that means sharing your story when it feels right, when you want to, or when it will help you. if you want to share your truth, yell it!! scream it from the rooftops!! use your previous pain & suffering to educate!! but- never feel like you have a responsibility to put a hold on your healing process/self-care/mental health in order to be an activist for others and to others. 🌻i’ve said it before and i’ve said it again- the greatest act of rebellion a survivor commits against the patriarchy each and everyday is by existing. and that is beautiful. and that is enough. 🍄 allies/loved ones- don’t push survivors to tell their story if they’re obviously uncomfortable or unwilling. you, as an ally, are there to be there as a column of support and to listen if & when they are ready to share. you, as an ally, are there to treat them normally. you pushing them to tell their story is more anxiety-inducing and further sets back the goal of regaining self control rather than empowering. some of the greatest empowerment takes place when all is silent. 🌙

text:
as much of a romantic i am, i'd never think i'd marry a guy who consistently moves mountains to be with me. we are doing 8 cities in 2 weeks this time -- mostly for my film productions and engagements, and one of his. if a guy says he can't move to be with you, i'd think twice! in life and in relationships, it all goes down to priorities.
•
the fallen world we live in of #metoo⁠ ⁠today stems so much from the depriotization and devalue of womanhood - underpinning it all is the reduction of womanhood to mere biology. from pittance maternity leave to exorbitant childcare, our society is already clear about where women stand. i'd put it to the men of our house to tilt the balance over in restoring this. the reality is, you don't value what you don't prioritize.
•
as we work through our young marriage, vision for family, god-breathed dreams, and gaps in the world to stand in, this past year has been ever so fundamental and mad challenging in making unpopular choices, just trusting in the spirit, and being very very brave 😘 @edwardyounglee you're my rockstar. #edplusjan #livingmypromiseland

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
day 6: today's post is on the emotion, fear.

her day care is a nice, safe place and yet, the doubt if she is okay stays at the back of the mind all the time. sometimes, i fear that i might lose her in a shopping mall, if my focus shifts from her for a few seconds. and then, there are times when i think of how her school life would be. would she be bullied, would she be in bad company, would she treat me like an enemy, would her first love break her heart, and so on. i know that i can get paranoid at times.

anyway,  the #metoo movement around the world and especially in india showed the real colors of some of the famous people, and also of the society as a whole. either in the us or in india, the questions are always directed towards the victims. i would need a separate post just to talk about the #metoo movement.

my real fear right now is, if tanvi would restrict herself because of this judgemental society. i do not want her to confine her thoughts and actions just because she assumes that her voice and actions don't make a difference. i do not want her to feel influenced by ideas or practices just because they had been prevalent due to cultural or patriarchal reasons. i do not want her to give up on the values that she will develop in the coming years. i do not want her to set a boundary for herself or stop asking questions. 
i don't know if i'm even making sense. but, when i was growing up, though i had enough freedom relative to my other girl cousins, to talk my mind and have my way, i confined myself in a shell, because of the conservative society that i grew up in. i had imposed some restrictions on myself assuming that i'm going against the norm, the norm that i've been seeing all along in the society. i hope tanvi is all that i was not.

i hope she is not scared to make mistakes, to be adventurous, to speak her mind, to stand up for what is right, to explore everything, to question injustice and to be herself. i hope to help her as she grows up to be a courageous person who triumphs over her fears and her mother's. :) #fear #courage #tanvisbirthday #birthdayweek #thesinkisalwaysfull #motherhood #love #adulting #motherdaughtergoals #bff #bestfriends

text: sorry about the pause. i grew up near thousand oaks, where the california shooting took place last week. my parents still live in that area so it was a lot to take in. then the next day the fires started and my  parents had to evacuate and stay with me. which is fine because earlier in the week i broke up with a boyfriend i loved because the reality is, we fundamentally just couldn’t work. i could obsess on any of these things and in some ways i am. mostly, i just am trying to appreciate how things are right now. there’s still goodness among such horrible shit. there’s things to be thankful for, like all of you coming here to go on this journey with me. i’m not sure what the future holds in store for me or you or any of us. hopefully, we’ll each get where we’re going and change the world for the better in the process. #sexism #feminism #feminist #timesup #metoo  #genderequality #womensupportingwomen #girlgang #girlsquad #strongwomen #selfconfidence #mentalhealth #selflove #intersectionalfeminist #intersectionalfeminism #intersectional #intersectionality #allinclusive #allinclusivefeminism #allinclusivefeminist #girlpower #bodypositivity #intersectionalbodypositivity #allinclusivebodypositivity #ladypower #womenareawesome #womenhavepower

text: så jäkla mäktigt! 💪💣💥 @regran_ed from @ninarungs -  kvinnor har kämpat för jämställdhet inom alla samhällets områden i decennier. i århundraden. också nu under #metoo är det kvinnorna som dragit lasset. som berättat, stöttat och krävt förändring. kvinnor som steg för steg förändrar världen. och som adresserar problemet och ser lösningarna. att idrottsvärlden har en del att brottas med är ju känt sen länge. kvinnor som spelar fotboll har en tiondel av männens löner. får jobba och plugga samtidigt som de spelar i högsta division medan killar och män får chans att satsa. tjejer som får hålla tillgodo med sämre träningstider, anläggningar och anpassa sig till en jargong om hur kärringar spelar. ändå står kvinnor som @fischernilla där. som förebilder för nästa generation som kanske kanske får det bättre. och det kommer tyvärr inte vara männens förtjänst utan kvinnornas. igen. men tack för att ni finns. nu hoppas jag bara att några eller någon av alla herrspelare ska bli i alla fall lite engagerad mot sexism och för jämställdhet. det har vi alla allt att vinna på ✊ - #regrann

text:
that’s what qanon followers really want, after all. that’s where their “storm” motto comes from. most americans were puzzled when, in a meeting with military leaders months ago, trump said, “you know what this represents? maybe it’s the calm before the storm.” but these theorists thought they knew exactly what he was talking about. trump was pointing at the officers’ uniforms.

the storm qanon truthers predict will never strike because the conspiracy that obsesses them doesn’t exist. but while they wait for it, they’ll try to whip up the winds, and the rest of us will struggle to find shelter. qanon is scary because it’s getting bigger, it’s scary because we don’t know how to stop it, and it’s scary because the people behind it won’t be stopped, and, until their illusory storm arrives, they won’t be satisfied.

molly roberts
the washington post

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
d a n c e // the color of our scars
#advocate #idaho ——————————————————————
1 of 2
last week, we had the colors of our scars at the romance theater in rexburg and it was an amazing show. show attendance was great too — thank you! here are a few images from the performances and speakers. 
we are thankful for the dancers and choreographers, speakers, the community, and anyone who had part in making this show possible. it all came together so well! 
the colors of our scars addressed and interpreted domestic abuse through dance. its main purpose was to raise awareness and help us all recognize unhealthy relationships in our lives. the color of our scars went even deeper than that and told a story about finding joy in our darkest and hardest experiences by focusing on the brighter colors of our lives. 
we can all change the colors of our scars. 
thanks for all the support! —————————————————————— #lifestyle #family #loveshouldnthurt #october #enddv #byui #dvfacts #dancing #entrepreneur #fall #design #wellness #marketing #friends #idaho #timesup #metoo #health #breakthesilence #idaho #graphicdesign #healthy #dance #healthy

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
in the youth of our fury. in a world where we need to be socially conscious . 
two souls met on an evening night out... he was observant and charming. i was intrigued. 
beautiful he is beautiful enough for me. the sun hit his yellow house just like if it was a sign from god. 
i'm relieved

i saw the feminine presence in a man' eyes. it means he is in peace. i do not have to bring to him -ease

i then decided to undress his conscience and make love to his thoughts. and in return he touch the inner of my soul -we call it love. 
it's silly to think of unborn children.cause all i am thinking about is the day that i will be able to know'em. tell them that since the very beginning they were desire. our souls painted the blank pages together . it's only that day when life will grow into me . that i will finally feel complete. i believe that everyone deserves the chance to meet their poem. their soulmate . - l.r

text:
keep california in your hearts and prayers 🙏 
these are pictures i had taken on my year anniversary of leaving treatment at the serra retreat center in malibu... they posted yesterday the retreat had not burned and i was so happy to hear that. 
i went to church, was married and confirmed at our lady of malibu and had various retreats there over the years and think it's the most beautiful and peaceful place in the world. it's simple and quaint and has amazing views and a labyrinth. 
two years ago after my missed meeting i was lost, confused and scared. my good friend, who is here again this year, invited me to malibu for thanksgiving and i jumped at the chance. i remembered the retreat and the labyrinth and decided to visit during the trip. 
the night before leaving was thanksgiving and my brother and i got into a big fight and i was very upset. as i was packing i found this small piece of paper and was so confused. 
as i looked closer it was a labyrinth and i got a weird feeling. i had not seen this before and it was in my suitcase. at that time i was traveling every week so i was using my suitcase constantly. i was walking a labyrinth the next day, it was so weird 
this message made me take the meditative walk very seriously and eventually i determined i needed professional help. imagine my surprise when my therapist in boise recommended passages in malibu and when i called they accepted my insurance. 
the universe sent me back to malibu to heal and now this special place is in danger. let's pray for the fires to end 🙏

#prayformalibu #prayforcalifornia #malibulove #meditation #labyrinth #sober #nohangover #noalcohol #metoo #mentalhealth #teetotaler #sober #nohangover

text:
this year has been a year of truly valuing myself: body, mind, spirit and health. my faith has played an important role & i believe more than ever that god's timing is the one to trust. i have learned so much & i've been feeling in my heart to push myself to new areas that i've always dreamt of pursuing. i want to invite each & everyone of you on this path with me. your voice is the strongest thing & i pray that god has given me this adventure to help those who need guidance & someone to talk through their pain. 
through this new adventure i am excited to help those in more areas of life! from faith, lifestyle, running, health and body...no one should be alone in pursuing their own personal growth. i am thankful for this team that i am surrounded by. #thevoyagelife .

.

text:
just had the incredible privilege of hearing tarana burke, the founder of the #metoo movement, talk. 
she spoke of how the movement began (in the 90s, believe it or not), how she came to be an activist, as well as the challenges of the movement before and in this internet era. 
some highlights from her talk:

women and the oppressed lived in a veil of shame. but now we live in a world where we can talk about sexual violence out loud.

#metoo is more than just an internet movement. it's grassroots, looks different in different countries, and is about centering on survivors. 
we need to start w the premise that survivors are telling the truth, to take their stories seriously and afford them the dignity/humanity. 
it's about a redistribution of power, away from oppression and to the people that need it most. it's also about educating the youth around issues of respect, boundaries, body autonomy and the gender spectrum.

what an amazing hero for the times.
name: Jun Shen Chia

text:
//trigger warning.
•
in a dark bar
unsolicited
on a saturday 
i was told
that i’m too uptight. 
i should smile more. 
learn to let loose. have fun. 
i had to swallow the memories as they clawed their way up my throat
and out of my mouth.
i pressed them down
and tasted iron and metal
and pain and fear.
don’t let him see that you’re weak 
be a lady
loosen up
make yourself small.
“from what i’ve heard, your problem is that you don’t know how to have any fun” he said, hands squeezing my shoulders, 
like he was trying to help. 
lend some advice,
with a wink
and a smile. 
my memories threw rocks at the inside of my throat
my fists clenched around my drink as my weekend turned into
a war field 
did your source tell you
that his idea of fun
is a human game 
of cat
and mouse?
did he tell you that when i close my eyes
and try to sleep
i can still feel his breath on the side of my cheek
while he knelt
at the edge
of the bed
with regret
“i’m sorry 
so sorry. 
i’m so sorry” 
but all i could hear
was my own voice
begging him
to stop 
all i could feel
was arms locked and shoulders pinned and throat choked 
and no no no 
and terror and 
please 
don’t let this end 
the way my nightmares 
always do. 
thank god
my voice remembered 
how to speak.
my body froze 
but my lips
were not too uptight
to remember 
how to say
stop.
so if this is your idea of fun,
then my idea of fun
is keeping pepper spray 
in my nightstand. 
if this is your idea of fun
then you’re right,
i’m not having it.
and if that makes me uptight
then i will smile 
and nod
and agree.
because your source 
is not my concern
anymore
and this story
will end 
differently. 
i will no longer bury
the broken glass
he left behind
so his feet can escape quietly
i have too many sisters
trying to move forward
with bleeding souls
inside of their shoes.
i see you, sister,
heart still open, but bruised.
i see you, sister,
and i’m walking
forward
with you.
|mh 📸 @gleanandco hmu @bygorjess|

text: in my vows.... i told amanda i promise to keep life exciting. with my spontaneous trips. and crazy ideas. i purchased these tickets to the angel band project charity event. because her number one idol mariska was hosting. and she had never officially met her. but also because i wanted to support victims of sexual assault. mariska sat next to us for an hour. literally next to us. in a room of 100 people. and i got the balls to turn around half way through and thanked her for all that she has done for victims and survivors. i told her amanda and i came there for her. amanda was acting like she wasnt paying attention... but mariska looked at her and said "hi!!" with her hand out. 😂🤣 i made my wifes dream come true tonight. which brings me to tears. but more so... we supported an amazing cause. and as a survivor myself.... i just wanted to say 1 in 5 women are a victim. #metoo thank you for an amazing night @therealmariskahargitay @norbert_leo_butz @theangelbandproject

text:
💜 👑 so many thoughts run through my mind on the daily but above any and everything else that i may truly need or just desire to have, peace of mind is most valuable to me. that can't be found without first knowing myself and loving myself. i haven't always done that but i do now and i'm making up for lost time. my value and worth has increased and is steadily rising. i am not the same person i was yesterday, or 20 minutes ago or even 5 seconds ago. not everyone is worthy of my time and energy. i know that now. im still a person who loves fiercely, but i can no longer be a martyr to any one or anything. nothing should cost me my self worth, my dignity, my hopes and dreams, my sanity, my peace of mind. i have come so far... i still have miles to go...but believe me, i will get there!  #shesmiles ☺#sheslays 💁

text:
it’s a distraction!!
~
.
i have been deeply thinking about what a ridiculous waste of talent, potential, innovation and progress bias is in our society and at the workplace. it literally robs us of our individual, national and corporate competitive advantage. ~
.
toni morrison said quote “it’s important, to know who the real enemy is, & to know the function, the very serious function of racism, which is distraction. it keeps you from doing your work. it keeps you explaining over and over again, your reason for being. somebody says you have no language & so you spend 20 years proving that you do. somebody says your head isn’t shaped properly so you have scientists working on the fact that it is. somebody says that you have no art so you dredge that up.
~
.
she talks about racism & it applies to all forms of bias including gender. one of the things this #metoo movement is about is that we women just want to exercise our god given right to bring our brilliance, contribution, innovation, creativity and ultimately our best selves to work. dealing with harassment, is a distraction. having good men also scared to have a healthy collaborative work relationship with women is also a distraction. ~
.
let’s fix all these distractions so we can move on to focus on bringing our brilliance to the world and to the workplace #irefusetoletyoudistractme ~
.
#diversity #unconsciousbias #assimilation #shame #difference #differentiator #metoo #woke #bilingual #diversityandequity #bilingual #latina #inclusion #tonimorrison #racism #lifecoach #discrimination #careercoach #executivecoach #immigrant #harassment #distraction #womeninbusiness #leadership #blackgirlswhoblog #blackgirlmagic #latina #afrolatina #womenempowerment #yourpowerunleashed

text: painting every day. i feel like i am starting to develop my style. i thought for years that i had peaked in high school. i had this amazing concentration for ap art and haven’t found the groove in 15 years. but now i feel my true calling is storytelling. my first concentration was my journey to self identity and now i have found another person’s story to tell. i hope that i am portraying it with the beauty and honor that it deserves #finn #blacksheepfinn #finntheartist #blacksheep #blacksheepcreatives #blacksheepartist #blacksheepartistcollective #art #artist #atlanta #georgia #fayette #fayetteville #fayco #fayettecounty #pinewoodforrest #pinewood #local #talent #veteran #veteranartist #metoo #acrylicpainting #myart #painting #inspired #love #mymuse

text:
today is monday. monday is the day where half the day i work on things i am commissioned to do, and the other half the day i work on things related to home or self care. 
for my self-care today, i made this soup. 
self-care is so important to me and it is vital to my productivity and survival. 
some of you know this, and some of you might be reading and learning this for the first time but to manage the effects from the physical and emotional trauma i experienced as a child, along with the very real conditions of our world today, -i take medication to lower my blood pressure, to alleviate anxiety, to block histamine and to coat the lining of my stomach -i use creams/tonics for my hair, skin, nails, joints & teeth
-i eat gluten free, lots of vegetables, “clean-er”, and with as little red meat and dairy as possible -i laugh, sweat, dance, run & sing daily
-i pray and write everyday -i say, “thank you” often -i talk to/text/see my loved ones often -i end the day with either a glass of red wine or an up, dirty martini -i surround myself with a very small circle of friends
-i remove myself from toxic situations and people as soon as possible
-i celebrate every.little.thing.
-i enjoy life
-i do work that challenges me and the world to be better -i am a minimalist and have very few physical attachments or material possessions -i use all parts of my brain equally to simultaneously interpret, create, engage, & navigate situations
-i drink lots of water
-i enjoy things that activate my senses -i only watch world news outlets -i do not watch tv (just hulu, reuters, & netflix)
-i create systems, structures and lists to manage all aspects of my life and calendar
-i enlist help from the village when i need it -i take naps often -i release pain and disappointment through breath, many breaths...
-to relax, i do something that requires my singular focus like jigsaw puzzles, making crafts, painting, and cooking! 😋
-i articulate my appreciation for those who bless me, and i reciprocate -i treasure those life-giving connections

#sabbath #yum #nofilter #glutenfree #shift #mentalhealth #mentalhealthawareness #removethestigma #metoo #loveyourself #loveyourselffirst

text:
it’s sad that so many women can expect to experience some sort of sexual assault. that’s pretty disturbing. and even though it’s less, men (probably more boys) can expect it as well. we shouldn’t feel like this. period. and what makes it worse is when society doesn’t support or believe victims. it has to stop.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
my project, our stories matter, is a way for everyone to be heard and others to understand more about their experiences. victims of assault, abuse, rape, and domestic violence have voices and we need to listen and support them. i’ve also teamed up with licensed psychotherapist @cosmicchristine to help provide a safe place for people to come forward and open up. i am so grateful to have her on board and for sharing her own stories of abuse.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

text: the story of progress as i am starting to paint again. every woman has a story— this is one of love and healing. i want to be able to tell her story and do it well. the relevance of the #metoo movement is harrowing and it is not just a story of the victims and aggressors but also of the loved ones of those people— and therefore it is my story too. in all of this i just want one of the men accused to just say “i’m sorry” without a continuance of abuse due to some power play or pride or consequence. #finn #blacksheepfinn #finntheartist #blacksheep #blacksheepcreatives #blacksheepartist #blacksheepartistcollective #art #artist #atlanta #georgia #fayette #fayetteville #fayco #fayettecounty #pinewoodforrest #pinewood #local #talent #veteran #veteranartist #myart #mymuse #acrylic #acrylicpainting #love #storytelling #painting

text:
you will never forget your first fight with a narcissist. the distractions and irrelevant semantics will blow your mind.
.
sometimes i would just cry because he wouldn’t say a word. he’d just stare straight ahead completely frozen. it was like watching a person dissociate and go somewhere else. other times he had this puzzling rage where his logic made no sense. his arguments were highly defensive and completely irrational. at one point i seriously considered buying him a dictionary. words he did not understand the definition of: irrational, logical, loyalty, success, love, lying, basic human decency, narcissist, sociopath. 🤯💛🦋

han pasado más de 20 años y el caso se ha archivado hasta en cuatro oportunidades, pero el día de hoy la fiscal marcelita gutiérrez formuló denuncia penal por el caso de esterilizaciones forzadas, el mismo que incluye dentro de los acusados al ex presidente alberto fujimori y sus ex ministros costa, aguinaga, young y otros.

desde ni una menos arequipa, les enviamos a todas las sobrevivientes un gran abrazo sororo y decirles que no están solas, que su lucha esta cambiando la historia de muchas mujeres que anhelaban justicia.

text:
#whyididntreport 
i’ve had quite a few people tell me i shouldn’t be posting this sort of “stuff” that i will be looked down upon and could even affect the way my children are treated by peers, teachers, family, friends and friends parents. but here’s the issue, talking about being a victim of rape and sexual abuse is a very “taboo” subject, and it shouldn’t be. the problem with this way of thinking about rape is that it places blame on the person who had to endure it versus the perpetrator. i spent the majority of my life listening to over and over and hearing his voice tell me it was my fault and him rationalizing what he did to me the night before as if it was a valid reason and unfortunately i believed it. this began years and years of trying to cover up the person i was inside, to try and hide myself away and make myself disappear little by little. i was hiding under a blanket of deep shame trying to forget my inner self that was just beginning to blossom as a teenager coming into a woman. then began years and years of self harm and self hatred and struggling with suicide. i was so fortunate to have my son at 19 and i was able to delve my entire worth and life into being a mom. my son saved me, but eventually everything catches up with you. as the kids grew older my mind that had once desperately tried to cover up these wounds inflicted, by putting myself into being a mother, well they started to peek through and make their self known and that feeling grew and grew, and i tried and tried to ignore their calls. well they caught up, and all that completely unresolved hurt, shame, guilt, pain and fear would not be ignored any longer. i had to face the reality of what i had so desperately tried to forget. and maybe had i come across another persons feelings or similar story to what i was going through i could have potentially gotten the help i needed. i will no longer be ashamed of what was done to me, i was a kid and if that changes someone’s perception of me well, so be it. no one no one deserves to be raped and sexually assaulted whether you’re a man, woman, transgender or no gender etc. 
#iwillnotbesilenced #iwontbeshamed #17yearoldme #itwasntmyfault #metoo

text:
#metoo 🙌🏼🔥✅💯👀 i can’t wait to work for myself full time so i don’t have to worry about being sexually harassed at my job. ⁣
⁣
👉🏼let’s back up.👈🏼⁣
thankfully i work for an employer who is understanding, doesn’t tolerate it and looks out for me. #blessed⁣
⁣
but when you get comments as someone is walking behind you, or sexual comments about what he would do... that draws a hard fucking line.⁣ 🤯🤬😤
⁣
i have to remain semi professional.⁣
i have to deal with the fact that this patient is back in the practice after being gone for 4 years. ⁣
⁣
✨when i work for myself?✨⁣
i don’t have to worry about being uncomfortable at work or nervous to help someone. ✨i work with who i choose.⁣✨
⁣
mark my words. ☝🏼💯✅⁣
that day is coming soon.⁣

text:
"sou pessoa de dentro pra fora. minha beleza está na minha essência e no meu caráter. acredito em sonhos, não em utopia. mas quando sonho, sonho alto. estou aqui é pra viver, cair, aprender, levantar e seguir em frente.
sou isso hoje...
amanhã, já me reinventei.
reinvento-me sempre que a vida pede um pouco mais de mim.
sou complexa, sou mistura, sou mulher com cara de menina... e vice-versa. me perco, me procuro e me acho. e quando necessário, enlouqueço e deixo rolar...
não me dou pela metade, não sou tua meio amiga nem teu quase amor. ou sou tudo ou sou nada. não suporto meio termos. sou boba, mas não sou burra. ingênua, mas não santa. sou pessoa de riso fácil... e choro também!" body @xerrimodaintima

text:
i have been thinking for quite sometime about posting this picture and explaining the reason. it’s incredibly difficult but i won’t be silent anymore. i am breaking free.
‼️
trigger warning.
‼️
my name is jennifer rodriguez-nieves and i am a sexual assault survivor.
•
my trauma started 7.5 months ago and it finished exactly 6 months ago. my trauma lasted a month and a half. my trauma included being drugged, abused and kidnapped. my trauma left me feeling powerless and worthless. my trauma changed me.
•
i never thought i was going to survive; i never thought i was going to be rescued by god, my husband and family.
•
the journey since then has been near impossible but i have continued regardless. god walks with me now more than ever.
•
this is exactly why i am taking self-defense classes, changed my habits, started a new life with my husband, created a blog and became the no.1 fan of our heavenly father.
•
has the trauma ended? unfortunately, no. i relieve it over and over again. nonetheless, i haven’t stopped fighting and i never will. i am now in control of my life, i have my power back and there is nothing greater than the protection of god.
•
i am beautiful, powerful and capable. i will get through this.
•

text:
adaptability. if you know me personally, you know my story is nothing short of challenge and tragedy.

strong with cyd is not just a cute name. for me, it symbolizes resilience, tenacity, patience, perseverance, hope, faith, love.

i know i’m not the only one.

i know there are other women who might have grown up feeling abandoned, confused, insecure, and unlovable because their daddy didn’t show up for them.

i know other women have been violently abused, bullied, or bruised.

i know a lot of women can attest to #metoo.

i know other women know what it feels like to cry themselves to sleep.

i know there are people who fight their own brains on a daily basis.

i know there are men measuring themselves to standards that seem impossible.

i know there are women filling themselves with sex to replace the love they never had.

i know what it feels like to put on a physical, and metaphorical mask every morning.

i’ve learnt that those who keep going are also, usually, the ones who last.

the people who see their world shifting, and find a way to shift with it.

the strong survive because they keep moving, they keep loving, they keep hoping, they don’t stop trying.

i know my struggles, my tears, my brokenness and my failures are not just my own.

i’m no different than anyone else, and my story of #strength is a story shared by us all.

we are strong because we choose to be. and we’ve got so much more to journey.

#strongwithcyd

text:
#mantramonday “we are all one.”
the lines we draw keep us from our power.
.✨
to admit you’ve been abused by a man doesn’t mean you hate all men. #metoo
.✨
to demand fair treatment from law enforcement doesn’t mean you think all police are bigots or that their lives don’t matter. #blacklivesmatter .
.✨
to disagree with our presidents tone is not to separate ourselves from everyone who identifies with him. 
#democrat #republican #liberal .
.✨
we all have our causes and beliefs.  but that doesn’t mean we “hate” the other side. .
.✨
we might see a body we “wish we had.” ... a lifestyle or advantage others possess that we desire... .
.✨
it can feel like we are merely islands of flesh and consciousness... but what is true is that we all come from one energy source and we all return to that source... our earth, our bodies and minds we are all literally part of one whole. .
.✨it may seem like we must #compete to #win...
but truly, the more separate we feel, the worse we feel... and that feels like a loss to me.
.
.
every time i hear something that makes me cringe-
“we are all one.”
every time i feel less than-
“we are all one.”
when i feel like i’m in an un-winnable race-
“we are all one.”
when a glimpse of the news breaks my heart again-
“we are all one.”
..
because who am i racing? 
no one. 
who am i less than?
no one.
what good will hating do to heal our wounds? 
well- not a damn bit of good. 
so i remind myself often-
“we are all one.”
✨and i instantly feel more calm... the solution more clear.✨
.
.
#wordsarepowerful 
#mantra
#weareallone
#loveistheanswer
#om
#omshanti

text: i believe the stories that have recently surfaced, starting with @cerclecheung and rapidly accumulated about cristian buitron (@cbtrn formerly) assaulting models. i did a shoot with him several years ago, after he took some pictures of me at a @bodyandpole party. some snippets of the experience: before i went to meet him he told me not bring any people with me, going out to long island, getting in his car, being driven to his house while he told me tales of his jiu jitsu prowess. he offered me a drink and i declined. he name dropped dancers. while doing the body paint, i asked to do some areas by myself, this surprised him but he said yes. after the body paint set up we went to the beach. nothing worse than a vague sense of unease (fueled by questionable comments from him) happened during my shoot. i was lucky. it had nothing to do with what i did or didn’t do. i’m sharing this story because it illustrates the pattern other women have described. i’m so glad y’all have bravely shared your stories. the pole/dance/aerial community will become a safer place because you’ve spoken up. #cristianbuitronphotography #cristianbuitron #bodyandpole #timesup #nycart #nycpole #poledance #metoo

text:
le labo #rose31 it excites me to have searched this place out and just stand in here and smell the air! 
#
the 2 guys that worked there #francois and #sebastien were ready to have all manner of conversation with me - body dysmorphia (in men), #metoo, taking things personally, perception and perspective depending on where you’re standing, travel, friendship and bonds...how refreshing that people who want your business aren’t afraid to open up to you about their own opinions. 
it’s one of the things i’m loving the best (apart from the food, fashion, real coffee...ok ok never-mind, i love everything about paris 😂) this sense of not false “anglo-niceness”. they don’t give a shit in a way that’s perfect!
after asking has this been my experience with people while we’ve been here, sebastian suggests it’s something i invite as he tells me about the usual walls that parisians have up and the lengthy period it takes for them to build trust...(if this is true, i’m very pleased about it) i consider this to be a gift. 🤷🏽‍♀️
#
i’ll ponder on this as i plan my next adventure to paris. we’re winding down into the eve of our last day and last night before we head back across the pond.
#
#positivevibesonly #lelabo #lelabofragrances #lelaborose31 #stayinginthemomemt #heretoenjoyitall #parisinthefall #parisinnovember #scorpioseason #scorpiosinparis #behernow #herstory

and more surprises.

text:
they are exciting and give you what you’ve always longed for. the relationship builds fast & furious.
.
except that is not how a good relationship builds. it takes time to build intimacy.
.
relationships w narcissists build at lightening speed. you become best friends and inseparable. they will text you first thing in the morning and last thing at night. some even text a lot throughout the day. this ensures they are always on your mind.
.
this is how attachment builds and will make it very hard for you to leave. like a drug addict you will crave this attention and “love” (fake love) when they withhold it. you’ll do anything to feel this intensity again, so you keep going back. you keep improving your behavior. you keep adjusting things so you can keep this amazing intensity which you’ve been fooled into believing is intimacy..
.
dm  me for new group starting soon. bookstudy: healing from hidden abuse. let’s f this shit and get better!!!
.

text: meet the women whose persistence made texas a&m change its sexual assault policies. all had frustrating encounters with the administration after reporting their experiences of sexual assault and harassment, saying a&m handed out minor penalties for major infractions and led them through confusing and contradictory processes. now that they've spoken out, a&m has minimum and maximum sanctions for different sexual assault charges based on the severity of the violation, and students who are found responsible and suspended for a year can no longer remain on an athletic team or receive university-administered scholarships. the group of women who came forward, known as “twelfth woman” in deference to the school’s famed 12th man group of aggie football tradition, welcome these shifts in policy. but they're not sure if the university really wants to change—or if it just wants to rehabilitate its image after a rash of bad publicity. whatever happens, what they want from a&m now is an apology. visit the link in our bio to read the full story from dan solomon and jessica luther. 📷: @tamirhasacellphone #aggies #tamu #texasaggies #metoo

text: closing ceremony of #facingrace with a panel discussion led by the one and only john powell, in conversation with anat shenker-osorio, ash-lee woodard henderson, julie nelson, and tarso luis ramos. | title: is america possible? building a multiracial democracy in an era of division: “as the u.s. approaches 2043 and a demographic tipping point, right-wing demagogues of division are advancing their vision of white minority rule. how do we think about the struggle for a democratic future? what kinds of lessons can we draw from the global crisis of neoliberalism, beset by extreme economic and social inequality coupled with the rise of religious fundamentalism, misogyny, and racial and ethnic nationalism? how do we stop the march toward authoritarianism? in this plenary, leading thinkers and organizers discuss how we can advance the promise and possibility of a true multiracial democracy.” | so many great points and questions, it was hard to capture them all. here are just a few: ash-lee woodard henderson, “solidarity is a practice, not a theory. we gotta stick together, roll together, speak up for each other. when my ancestors said ‘by any means necessary,’ they said by all means” & john powell, “love has to be a part of the process.” | such a blessing to be a part of this community. #facingrace #facingrace2018 #raceforward #metoo #metoomovement #colorlines #racialequity #equity #racialjustice #justice #centerforsocialinclusion @centerforsocialinclusion @raceforward @colorlinesnews #ashleewoodardhenderson #johnpowell

text:
how do you show yourself?
.
.
i don’t know about you all, but i struggle to show the real me sometimes and in the past it’s been more than just sometimes. my path since i started work as a therapist has been to release myself from the weight of what others told me to be and just allow authentic magena ( <— that’s me) to come forward. i have tattoos and i’ll be getting more, i like big hoops, i wear ripped jeans, i struggle to be vulnerable but do it anyway... that’s how i show myself. that is how i elevate.
.
.
at the time i chose the name elevate psychological services i wasn’t sure why but it... well, it felt right. now i know why.  here is where you’ll find the time and space to rise up from the ashes; to; to break chains; to elevate. to be clear, there is no expectation of this, but opportunity. sometimes you elevate when you brushed your teeth today and you couldn’t yesterday or when you shared something you had hidden before. how do you elevate?
.
.  a special shout out to @light_and_shine_photography for helping me show myself. .
#metoo #psychotherapy #therapy #mentalhealth #recovery #psychology #counseling #mentalhealthawareness #growth #goals #therapyhelps #useselfcompassion #justbreath #selfrespect #loveyourself #loveyou #authenticity #authentique #authentic💯#levelup #stress #health #covina #westcovina #journey #trustyourjourney #journeytohealth #journeytowellness #journeyoflife

text:
おはよう。
なんだか季節の割に暖かいよね。もし、今、あなたが私のことを嫌いでも私はかまわない。
そんなことで私は嫌いにならないし、むしろ嫌ってくれる元気があなたにあることを喜ぶ。

good morning. today it is warm for the seasons too. 
if you do not like me now, i am fine. such a thing makes me hate you, i am delighted that you have a lot of energy to dislike me.

#metoo #remetoo #praisethebrave

text: kvinnor har kämpat för jämställdhet inom alla samhällets områden i decennier. i århundraden. också nu under #metoo är det kvinnorna som dragit lasset. som berättat, stöttat och krävt förändring. kvinnor som steg för steg förändrar världen. och som adresserar problemet och ser lösningarna. att idrottsvärlden har en del att brottas med är ju känt sen länge. kvinnor som spelar fotboll har en tiondel av männens löner. får jobba och plugga samtidigt som de spelar i högsta division medan killar och män får chans att satsa. tjejer som får hålla tillgodo med sämre träningstider, anläggningar och anpassa sig till en jargong om hur kärringar spelar. ändå står kvinnor som @fischernilla där. som förebilder för nästa generation som kanske kanske får det bättre. och det kommer tyvärr inte vara männens förtjänst utan kvinnornas. igen. men tack för att ni finns. nu hoppas jag bara att några eller någon av alla herrspelare ska bli i alla fall lite engagerad mot sexism och för jämställdhet. det har vi alla allt att vinna på ✊

text:
🌟🌸this is mi abuela, la mia nonna gloria the mother of my mum. it’s the only photo i have of her. she was a flight attendant for mexicana back in the day kind of when that whole scene was super hip. 
i never really got to know her when she was living. i only have one story of her holding me once. the rest of the stories i have are those of the broken and misunderstood relationship my mum and her had. my mum basically grew up without her mother, she would say to me that mi abuela had a severe mental illness. 
in my mid twenties my great uncle came to find me. he told me about that one time when gloria had accompanied him, my great tío lalo to the usa on a quick trip and how unfortunately she was raped at the border. my mum was just a child at the time the youngest of 4 siblings. 
my abuela did not suffer from a mental illness. my nonna was sexually abused in a time where there was no support for this kind of stuff and very much tabu to even be able to share this experience with family or community. 
#metoo i write these words as a prayer into the ethers of cyber space as she has asked me to do for her and hope that we can honor her pain in a warm embrace, understand and support her as the beautiful strong woman that she is.

🌟🌸this is mi abuela, la mia nonna gloria the mother of my mum. it’s the only photo i have of her. she was a flight attendant for mexicana back in the day kind of when that whole scene was super hip. 
i never really got to know her when she was living. i only have one story of her holding me once. the rest of the stories i have are those of the broken and misunderstood relationship my mum and her had. my mum basically grew up without her mother, she would say to me that mi abuela had a severe mental illness. 
in my mid twenties my great uncle came to find me. he told me about that one time when gloria had accompanied him, my great tío lalo to the usa on a quick trip and how unfounately she was raped at the border. my mum was just a child at the time the youngest of 4 siblings. 
my abuela did not suffer from a mental illness. my nonna was sexually abused in a time where there was no suppo for this kind of stuff and very much tabu to even be able to share this experience with family or community. 
 i write these words as a prayer into the ethers of cyber space as she has asked me to do for her and hope that we can honor her pain in a warm embrace, understand and suppo her as the beautiful strong woman that she is.

text:
8 months maybe longer i have been in this state of sadness.  i didn’t even realise how much of a state till recently.  the more sadness i felt the more lost i seemed to become sinking deeper and deeper into my own head.  letting my negative thoughts beat me down till they were so loud that is all i could hear.  till they were so loud i became them.  till they were so loud i would look in a mirror and see them.  till they were so loud i would see me through eyes of hate rather than see me with love. 
i am not sure how what began my trip down this old haunted road.  what caused me to let my negative voices define me, they had a habit of sneaking up silently, catching me unawareness like a thief in the night till it was just too late. 
all the preparations, the tools i had learnt and still i became overwhelmed.  maybe i just became to comfy, too complacent, too cocky.

so here i sit 20kg heavier, physically and emotionally.  but i am ready to pick myself up and dust myself off.  de ja vu yes i have definitely been here before a lot!  i already hear the whispers “what makes you think this time is different?” ❤️ but one voice that stands out above the rest “ally don’t you dare quit!  your worth fighting for! ❤️ 💋

it’s not about how many times we fall what matters,  is that we get back up and that we keep trying no matter what. 🌻 “success is not in never failing, but rising everytime you fall!” - jonathan taylor thomas 🌈

#worthy #grateful #dontgiveup #keepgoing #getup #metoo #survivor #warrior #courage

text: #survivorsteps 💙 this may not seem like a big deal to a lot of you but these steps are critical for me. ptsd impacts the mind and body. the trauma that i have experienced caused me to become less and less active; almost to the point of not being physically active at all. when i actually leave the house, i have to take frequent breaks just from walking or standing. my body has become weak...but i am determined to make it strong. half a mile in 20 minutes might not seem like much but it's a big deal to me. i'm taking survivor steps. brave steps. i was hesitant to post this because my mind is trying to tell me that i won't keep it up. what if i post this and can't find the strength to keep it up? will i let those who love and support me down? all i can do is keep trying. keep fighting. survivor steps. 💙 #believesurvivors #ptsd #metoo #mindbodysoul #rehabilitation #iamasurvivor #stopsexualassault #iwontbesilent

text:
#metoo
i was sorting my sd cards and came across these photos i took for a uni assignment. they were shot in response to the #metoo movement.

they are meant to depict the shame a victim of sexual assault often feels, the sort that clings on and follows them around where ever they go, sometimes morphing into ptsd or depression.

i believe this shame is inflicted by society itself; with its many biases and selective hearing, it leaves so many by the wayside. the #metoo movement offers victims a relief from the shame within a community, will hopefully continue to fight misconceptions and provides hope that one-day things will be better for everyone.

i hope to live to see a world where victims of sexual assault feel no more shame than those of a mugging or a burglary or fraud and their accusations against the perpetrator are taken seriously and with respect.

#metoo #survivors #equality #artphotography #gameoftones #selfportrait
